title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in. Add flour with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour.
Put coconut in batter.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: In shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish combine potatoes, oil and black pepper.
Firmly press mixture across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes.
In the meantime brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in gravy mix, water and garlic powder and bring to a boil.
Stir in frozen mixed vegetables.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 can French fried onion rings. Pour this mixture into potato shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve with extra gravy if desired.

title: mostaccioli and sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain.
In a 2-quart baking dish, combine sausage, sauce, noodles and half of Mozzarella cheese, mixing well.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream oleo; add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Cool; roll in confectioners sugar again.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Place a single layer of whole graham crackers on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pudding mix with 3 cups of the milk, stirring until thickened.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread half the pudding mixture on graham cracker layer.
Add another layer of crackers.
Cover this with remaining pudding.
Top with third layer of crackers.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, butter, remaining milk, corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir over low heat just until liquefied.
Pour over top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate at least 28 hours.
May prepare 2 days before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, water, eggs, sugar and margarine.
Knead dough. Add chocolate chips.
Drop onto pan and cook a couple of minutes.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown and onion is tender; drain. Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano and salt.

Bring meat mixture to boiling; boil gently, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes. Stir occasionally. Remove meat sauce from heat. Stir in drained, cooked spaghetti. Place 1/2 of mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Top with remaining mixture. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet over medium heat.
Drain. In a large kettle, put beef and onion mix and all other ingredients.
Simmer until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Chop onions.
Cook butter, onion and bell pepper until tender. Add Ro-Tel and English peas.
Add salt and pepper.
Put 1/2 of cheese in with all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in slow oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put the other half of cheese over the casserole.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice in saucepan.
Mix flour, cinnamon and salt. Add to apple juice, cooking until thick.
Coat the apple slices with the apple juice mixture.
Fill pie crust with apples.
Dot with margarine.
Place top crust over apple mixture.
Sprinkle with water and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cola chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place pork chops in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. In a small bowl, mix together the cola and ketchup. Pour over chops and sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake uncovered for about 1 hour, or until pork is cooked through and internal temperature has reached 160°.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix water with yeast.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add flour and oil to yeast mixture.
Stir and form ball.
Place in oiled bowl, turn to coat.
Cover.
Let set in warm place until it doubles. Grease pizza pan.
Place dough in center of pan and spread dough to fit.
Add sauce and toppings of choice.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sensational shrimp spread
directions: Mix and beat ingredients until fluffy.	Chill and use on Melba rounds.
I cut small round circles of hard French rolls, then brush melted butter on sides and toast in the oven.

title: nectarine blitz torte
directions: Cream together the shortening and powdered sugar. Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spread in 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1 cup of sugar a little at a time and continue beating until stiff.
Spread over cake batter.
Sprinkle each layer with 1 tablespoon each of sugar and almonds.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Dice 2 cups of nectarines and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Place a layer of cake on serving platter, meringue side down, then nectarines and whipped cream; repeat. Serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and strain.
In large pot, combine beef with tomatoes, cottage cheese, 1/2 package cream cheese, dash each of salt, pepper and onion powder, 2 to 3 dashes garlic and pinch of oregano.
Stir and simmer (stir often).
Meanwhile, boil lasagne noodles until tender.
Shred Cheddar, Mozzarella and Swiss cheeses.
Strain noodles.

title: christmas pie
directions: Cook until thick and let cool.
Fold in 3 bananas and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into crust; put in icebox, then add 1/2 pint whipping cream with 1/4 cup sugar.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar and pecans.
Layer pineapple, blueberries and 1 cup sugar.
Layer dry cake mix, then pour the butter, sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken-vegetable salad(lite choice)
directions: Toss the first 7 ingredients with mayonnaise.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Garnish with capers and paprika.

title: olive spread
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Mash with a fork and add mayonnaise, pecans and olives.
Add olive juice and a dash of pepper.
Stir well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve on toast crackers.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan.
Allow to stand for 30 or more minutes.
Cook over gentle heat, stirring constantly, with wooden spoon.
In 2 to 3 minutes, sauce will thicken.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: indian summer casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef; add onion, salt, pepper and seasonings.
Cook noodles and set aside.
When meat mixture is done, add corn, soup, mushrooms, pimentos and cream cheese.
Mix well until cheese melts.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add noodles. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and baking powder and mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake in a greased, 11 x 7-inch pan twenty minutes at 350° or until brown. Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mexican stew
directions: Fry steak in lots of grease in a large pot. Add potatoes, onions, peppers, cumin, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Let fry until potatoes are done, then drain grease. Add tomato sauce and water and let simmer about 10 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine everything except whipping cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 8 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in whipping cream.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Store refrigerated.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all.
Use spring-form pan.
Grease pan with melted butter. Roll crushed graham crackers around pan.
Fill pan with mixture and place in another pan.
Pour water in outside pan until there is 1/2 inch of water standing in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake is lightly browned.

title: trish's quick cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
When you remove cake from oven, punch holes into the cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Spread chocolate pudding over top of cake.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, spread Cool Whip over cake and add sprinkles as desired.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and jar of marshmallow cream.
Add mint. Serve chilled.

title: big soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients as any other recipe.
Drop a teaspoon of dough on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a small jar or object dipped in milk and then in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: irish crowdie
directions: Lightly toast oatmeal under the grill, turning frequently. Allow to cool.
Whip cream until firm and frothy, but not stiff. Stir in powdered sugar, toasted oatmeal, whiskey (or rum), vanilla essence and most of the raspberries, reserving some for decoration.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together; let set a while before serving.

title: pickles
directions: Combine lime in 2 gallons of water.
Soak cucumbers in lime overnight (24 hours).
Rinse in cool water changing every hour, 4 times.
Combine vinegar, salt, sugar
and pickling spice.
Add cucumbers and allow to soak another 24 hours.
Cook for 1 hour, pack in jars and heat seal.

title: butterscotch morsel cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven for approximately 12 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix butter, flour, sugar and baking powder like pie crust. Add the egg mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan (12 x 15-inch).

title: savory mushroom caps
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until slightly softened.
Add cream cheese and stir.
Add bread crumbs, lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture (mushrooms should be washed and laid on paper towel to dry until needed).
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be put under broiler if you want them browned more.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda in bowl.
Add egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Grease and flour 2 pie plates; divide batter.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fabulous curry dip
directions: Blend with mayonnaise in order listed.
Use as dip for all types raw vegetables: celery sticks, carrot sticks, cauliflower, radishes, etc.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spread 1 can crescent rolls flat in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: asparagus with green onion vinaigrette
directions: Make sauce by placing lemon juice, salt, pepper (as desired), green onions and olive oil in a blender or food processor; process until completely smooth.
Set aside.

title: mock lobster sandwich
directions: Spread 1 slice bread with deviled ham.
Slice a smallish pared cucumber lengthwise.
Place on deviled ham.

title: cheese soup
directions: In microwave, heat chicken broth.
Cook the noodles.
Saute onion in margarine in large pot on stove.
Add broth and noodle mixture.
In microwave, cook 1 package chopped broccoli (4 to 6 minutes) in package.
Add to large pot.
Melt Velveeta in 1 pint of half and half in microwave at medium temperature.
Add to noodle pot.
Stir all together.
Season with garlic salt and parsley.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon.
Fry potatoes in bacon grease with onions until tender.
Add crumbled bacon and season to taste.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Pour in uncooked rice.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Gently stir so ingredients are even.
Cook for one hour in a 350° oven.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix bulk sausage with packed biscuit mix.
Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add cheese to sausage mixture and stir to make an even blend of ingredients.
Make into tiny balls and freeze. Thaw when ready to bake on ungreased baking sheet in a hot 400° oven about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve piping hot. Yields 100 to 150 balls.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Core cabbage and parboil 20 minutes in a covered kettle.
Set aside to cool.
Combine ground beef, rice, egg and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Separate cabbage leaves.
Stuff meat mixture in cabbage leaf and roll up.
Spread sauerkraut on bottom of Dutch oven, then place layers of cabbage rolls on sauerkraut. Pour tomato juice over all.
Cover and cook 2 hours at 300°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: In a large bowl, add Jell-O (straight out of package) to cottage cheese and mix well.
Drain oranges and cut in half. Blend in Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: apple pumpkin muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in apples.
Fill greased muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until muffins test done.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield: 18 muffins.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler(yields 6 servings)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat until peaches are tender and mixture thickens.
Pour peach mixture into a lightly buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: hominy with chipotle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion in olive oil 1 minute.
Add garlic; cook 2 more minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, chipotle peppers and a little of the sauce.
These are hot; if you can't stand the heat, use 1 teaspoon tomato paste instead.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in hominy, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese, reserving 1/2 cup for the top.
Place casserole in the oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine dry cake mix, peach filling, lemon extract and nuts.
Blend at low speed until completely moistened, about one minute.
Beat two minutes at medium speed.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Add topping and bake for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-nut pudding
directions: Combine biscuit mix, pineapple and nuts.
Spread thin in bottom of greased baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Bring next 4 ingredients to boil and pour over dough.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut ice cream pie
directions: Bake one 9-inch pie shell; set aside.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, milk, flavoring and flour.
Drop onto greased pan.
Bake at 400°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese potato topper
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir in soup, sour cream and mustard and heat thoroughly.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in broccoli and heat.
Spoon over potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange-plus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the ingredients and pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and then turn out to cool.

title: beefy mexicali rice with cheese(makes 2 servings)
directions: In large skillet, bring water to boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese, breaking the meat into small pieces. Salt and pepper to taste.
Reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes. Stir occasionally.
(Rice should be tender and most of liquid absorbed.)
Top with cheese.
Cover and let stand 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: bubble bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread.
Grease angel food cake pan.
Cut bread in slices and the slices into little pieces.
Roll little pieces into balls and put in bottom of pan.
One loaf will cover bottom of pan.

title: "butterfinger ice cream"
directions: Beat 4 eggs.
Add sugar and mix.
Add vanilla and salt and whipping cream.
Put mixture and divider in container before adding Butterfingers, chopped.
Then proceed with ice cream maker directions using ice and salt.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: cheese twists
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, mustard, salt and red pepper in large bowl. Reserve 1 tablespoon cheese; stir remaining cheese into flour mixture. Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Add egg yolks and water, mixing until dough forms. Shape into a ball; flatten and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix melted butter, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Cover bottom of pan (angel food pan or Bundt pan).
Tear off chunks of dough (walnut size) and roll into ball.
Drop into pan.
Pour butter mixture over top.
Repeat process until dough is used.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.
(Poor Man's Sticky Buns.)

title: sausage-cheese chips
directions: Coarsely chop kielbasa; saute.
Arrange chips on greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese evenly over each chip.
Top with chilies.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Mix milk, salt, mustard and eggs and pour over other ingredients, tossing lightly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° for a souffle breakfast.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole dish or glass pie pan. Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with sesame seed crackers or wheat thins.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Combine butter, garlic, Worcestershire and lemon juice.
Put on low heat until butter is melted.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Salt and pepper chicken; dip into butter, then in crumbs. Pour any remaining sauce over chicken and sprinkle with any remaining crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover and continue baking for approximately 20 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute diced onion in butter until done.
To onion, add the Cheez Whiz.
When melted, add milk, salt and pepper.
Butter a glass baking dish.
Start with small about of melted cheese mixture in dish and alternate layers of cooked macaroni cheese, ending with shredded cheese.
Top with crushed croutons and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: easy banana cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar. Add butter, eggs, bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients with a fork until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on a bed of lettuce or in a pita pocket.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Beat well. Add Crisco and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and mix half with creamed mixture. Add the oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut, chips and nuts. Then add the rest of the flour. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage ryes
directions: Brown the meats.
Add cheese and cook until it melts.
Add seasonings and mushrooms; mix well.
Spread on slices of party rye.
Place on baking sheets and freeze.
After frozen, store in plastic bag.
To serve, heat under broiler until hot and bubbly.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and spread on bottom of pan. Mix together Rotel and add cream of mushroom soup. Spread
mixture over ground beef followed by the cheese. Cover the cheese with tater tots and bake about 20 minutes at 375 degrees. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Melt butter.
Add cocoa and Coke and bring to boiling.
Cool slightly and add soda to buttermilk.
Add cocoa mixture to sugar and flour.
Mix thoroughly and add buttermilk mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla with marshmallows to mixture.
Grease and flour pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease one bread pan. Mix first three ingredients together, pour into pan. Let raise 2-3 hours. Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Brush with butter and bake for 25 minutes more.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Cook sausage and crumble.
Drain off excess grease and place in the bottom of a greased baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together well.
Pour over sausage and bake in a 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill overnight or for several hours.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until well blended. Stir in flour, chocolate syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 16 squares. Remove from pan and store in airtight container.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients; add butter.
Cook on top of stove at medium heat, stirring all the time.
Slightly brown 8-inch pie crust.
When cocoa mixture has thickened, pour into pie crust.

title: bubble bread
directions: Partially thaw bread and cut into cubes.
Place in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cubes.
Let rise.
Bake at 350 for 30-40 minutes.
Loosen sides.
Remove from pan and invert onto platter.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix ingredients; beat well.
Let stand for 5 minutes; beat until creamy and frost cake.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Make chocolate pudding according to directions.
Add to dry cake mix and mix thoroughly.
Pour into oblong greased pan.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°.
Check after 35 minutes if toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Crush chips in package and mix half of chips with other ingredients.
Sprinkle last half on top of casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.

title: buttermilk noodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
In skillet, saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
In large bowl, combine noodles, mushrooms and onions; toss well.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in Marzetti's fresh buttermilk Ranch dressing.
Serve hot or cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain lima beans, but do not drain other beans.
Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Drain excess fat from skillet. Brown, then mix remaining ingredients.
Mix meat with beans and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and then 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together; add buttermilk.
Sift together flour and soda; add All-Bran.
Pour boiling water over Nabisco Bran; let cool.
Mix all together; set in refrigerator overnight.
(Do not stir batter after refrigerated.)
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed.
Refrigerate covered with paper towel, then plastic at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: apple-white grape juice punch
directions: Mix apple juice and white grape juice together. Freeze some for an ice ring. Before serving, add ginger ale and float ice ring.

title: onion dish
directions: Melt 1 stick butter.
Cook onions in butter until transparent. Mix soup and cornbread dressing.
Mix sour cream, pepper and corn.
Put a little cornbread mix on top.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge pecan pie
directions: In the top of a double boiler set over simmering water, melt together the chocolate and butter.
In a bowl, beat the eggs until frothy.
Gradually add the sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Slowly add the chocolate mixture until thoroughly blended.
Stir in the pecans.
Pour the mixture into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until the pie is flaky, about 35 minutes.
Do not chill.
Cool pie completely and serve with the whipped cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash the mushrooms and remove stems.
Lay mushroom caps with the insides up on an ungreased baking sheet.
Chop about 1/3 of the mushroom stems very fine and saute with the onion in the butter or margarine.
Remove from heat when onion is soft and let cool for a few minutes.
Mix in cheese, salami and ketchup.
Fill mushroom caps with this mixture either by spooning it on or if you have a cake decorating bag, this works nicely.
Sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs and bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Broil until brown, watching closely.

title: chocolate-covered frozen bananas
directions: You will also need popsicle sticks.

title: zucchini torta
directions: Slice zucchini and chop onion.

Parboil for about 15 to 20 minutes. Drain well. Cook Minute rice. Add all above ingredients and mix well. Save some grated cheese for top of torta. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch glass oblong dish. Remove from oven when top of torta is golden brown. Cool well before serving and cut into squares.

title: stove top macaroni and cheese
directions: In large heavy pan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add soup; gradually blend in water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat until cheese melts; stir often.
Makes about 10 1/2 cups.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Boil water.
Add Jell-O.
Stir in blueberries with juice, pineapple and pecans (congeal).
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add sugar.
Spread over congealed Jell-O.
Serve cold.

title: hot cranberry-banana punch
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium high heat, stirring until well blended.
Place four 4-inch squares of cheesecloth together. Place remaining ingredients in center and tie with string; add to punch.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Serve hot. Makes twelve 6 ounce servings.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Roast chicken or turkey in roasting pan with pan 1/2 full of water at 350° until done.
Cook corn bread in 8 or 9-inch skillet. Crumble corn bread in large bowl.
Add eggs, onions, celery, oleo, poultry seasoning, sugar or Sweet 'N Low, salt and light bread. Pour hot juice from chicken over this and take potato masher and mash real good (needs to be soupy).
Pour in baking dish and bake at 400° until firm.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour into melted oleo.
Do not stir.
Mix cherries and sugar and pour into other mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach very well.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with crackers or Hawaiian bread.

title: tiny tuna pizzas
directions: Combine tuna, chili sauce, onion, salt and oregano.
Mix well. Spread on rye slices of bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 4 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot.

title: applesauce crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in an 8-inch square pan.
Add vanilla, oil, water, honey (or sugar) and applesauce.
Mix well with fork, scraping sides to be sure that all the flour is mixed in.
Stir in either raisins and nuts or chopped apple.
Put in oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove pan from oven, using potholders or oven mitts.
Let cool before you cut it.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch flat, utility dish at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
After mixture has set overnight in refrigerator.

title: spicy cranberry punch
directions: Put spices (except cinnamon sticks) in top of percolator.
Add other ingredients to bottom of coffee maker. Perk punch and serve. Serve in punch cups and use cinnamon sticks for stirrers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: wine mushroom hamburger
directions: Combine beef, cream, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly with a fork until blended.
Shape into 3 or 4 thick patties.
Melt butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add patties; brown well on both sides.
Remove patties; keep warm. Add flour to drippings in pan; stir to blend well.
Add bouillon and wine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and becomes thick.
Add Worcestershire sauce, parsley and mushrooms with liquid.
Taste; add salt and pepper, if needed.
Return patties to sauce.
Simmer over low heat until meat is cooked to desired doneness.
Place meat patties on toast slices; pour sauce over the top.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken rolls
directions: * Can use pimento cream cheese in place of chopped pimento.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; microwave for 3 minutes.
Add peanuts; microwave for 3 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir in soda.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: rick's chicken wing sauce
directions: Cook butter slowly until melted. Add remaining ingredients; stir with a whip over low heat until hot. Place fried chicken wings in and shake. Serve.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan. Cook over low heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally. Increase heat to medium; bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute. Now is the time you would quickly add cherries and chocolate morsels. Stir until chocolate melts. Remove from heat; quickly stir in peanut butter until smooth. Stir in oats; quickly drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool completely. Carefully remove from wax paper. Store in airtight container. Yield: 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Shape the beef in 2 patties on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Top with potatoes, onions and carrots.
Wrap tight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese pouf
directions: At least four hours before serving (or may be done the day before) trim crusts from bread.
Grease a shallow casserole and layer bread slices, then cheese (cut in bite size pieces), then bread, then cheese.
Pour margarine over.
Beat eggs well.
Add salt, pepper, mustard and milk.
Pour over bread and cheese. Cover and refrigerate.
Put in 350° oven for 30 minutes covered, another 30 minutes uncovered.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Very moist and tasty.)

title: pumpkin and spice pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients except pastry shell.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in oven 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Continue baking 35 minutes or until knife inserted in the pie comes out clean.
Top with Ginger Whipped Topping. Serves 6.

title: apple cider biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir cider into flour mixture just until a soft dough forms that leaves the side of the bowl.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Beat eggs and milk together, then stir in dry ingredients.
Add melted butter. Drop from a spoon into pot of boiled greens or heated stock. Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until creamy.
The hardest part of this recipe is getting the Marshmallow Creme out of the jar.
I usually soak the unopened jar in hot water for a little while; it seems to make it easier to scrape out of jar.
Dip sliced apples or other fruit.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Place spices in a cloth and add to other ingredients.
Bring to boiling point and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with a stick of cinnamon.

title: perfect-easy pie crust
directions: Blend with electric mixer the shortening, flour, salt and sugar until crumbly. Add egg, vinegar and water. Mix with mixer until it is dampened. Form into balls and roll on a lightly floured board. This will make 4 or 5 flaky, tender pie crusts. Refrigerate before rolling if sticky.

title: cheese danish
directions: Save egg white to brush on cake and bake until it is brown. Cream the ingredients, except for rolls.
Pour into center of loaf.
(You could also use fruit with the cheese over it before closing.)
Bake at 350° until golden brown, for 20 or 25 minutes. Use a cookie sheet for baking.

title: cranberry applesauce
directions: Boil cranberries in 1 cup water until they burst and remove to large pot.
Add peeled and sliced apples, sugar and 1/2 cup water and cook until thick and soft on medium heat.
(Add more water for looser sauce.)
Serve hot or cold.

title: almond brittle
directions: Melt butter and
sugar until bubbly.
Line cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Lay
crackers
individually
on
cookie
sheet. Brush mixture of	butter and sugar evenly on crackers.
Sprinkle nuts on crackers.	Add
remaining butter mixture on nuts. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter or margarine in small mixing bowl.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency.
More milk may be added, if needed.
Makes 2 cups frosting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pour water over.
Work the flour, margarine and brown sugar together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder slowly to mixture.
May need to use a heavy mixer or a wooden spoon.
Add grated milk chocolate, pecans and chocolate chips.
Roll into small balls and place onto cookie sheet.
Bake 375 degrees for 6 minutes.
DO NOT OVER COOK OR THEY WILL BE HARD. BAKE ONLY 6 MINUTES AND THEY WILL BE VERY MOIST AND CHEWY.
THEY WILL NOT LOOK DONE WHEN YOU TAKE THEM OUT.
Makes 55 to 150 cookies, depending on size.

title: easy roast in foil
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Line shallow roasting pan with foil. Place meat in pan. Combine mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix. Spread over roast. Cover pan with foil.
Seal to edge. Bake in a 325° oven for1 hour.
Uncover and arrange potatoes and carrots around roast.
Cover and continue baking about 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender. Season to taste. Serves 8 to 12.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Place the bread, buttered on both sides, in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Brown sausage, drain and spread over the bread and top with cheese.
Repeat layers if desired.
Beat eggs, cream and milk. Add salt and dry mixture to egg.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese mixture.
Cover with foil; chill overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pink fluff
directions: Allow Cool Whip to soften.
Blend the Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk with mixer on medium speed.
Fold in pineapple, mandarin oranges, cherry pie filling, marshmallows and pecans. Garnish the top of "Pink Fluff" with crushed pecans.
The result is a pretty, easy to make and delicious salad.
(Remember to drain the oranges and pineapple.) Refrigerate.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Pour beans into large bowl. Add onion slices and pepper. Combine last 6 ingredients and pour over beans, onion and pepper. Toss gently. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Drain well and serve.

title: pan-browned potatoes
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, over medium-high heat, heat oil and butter.
Add enough potatoes to make a single layer in skillet. Cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a boil; repeat with remaining potatoes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat crescent rolls into bottom of pan for crust.
Beat eggs, water and onion.
Pour over crust (will barely cover).
Top with meat, then cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix and roll out (need not be chilled).
Cut into desired shapes and decorate.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Melt margarine and work in cream cheese.
Work in flour. Shape crust into tiny muffin tins and fill with pecans.
Beat egg and sugar and beat well.
Stir in margarine mixture, salt and vanilla.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture into each muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Make a ball the size of a quarter and roll in sugar. Repeat until cookie sheet is filled.
Press each cookie slightly with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Don't overbake.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Dissolve shortening, brown sugar and salt in hot water.
Add cold water, yeast and whole wheat flour.
Add enough white flour to make a slightly sticky dough (10 cups at most).
Knead.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Mix in eggs. Mix flour and baking powder and add all dry ingredients to sugar and oil, with milk.
Place in 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes, and simmer.
Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Add to meat mixture and simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve with corn bread or crackers.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: turkey or chicken strata
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Can be baked as soon as mixed if in a hurry.
Top with 1/2 cup American cheese.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: apple crisp(fresh apple)
directions: Pare, core and slice the apples into a bowl.
Take apples from water, place in a baking dish or pan, 13 x 10 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixed thoroughly with sugar; set aside and prepare topping.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter over low heat.
Remove and let cool slightly.
Add cocoa, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and spread in large pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: pig cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, oranges, butter and cake mix. Bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: one egg cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together well by hand for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
When cooled, serve with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: vitamin salad bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve cold.

title: chocolate caramel layer squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and butter.
Press half of cake mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over this layer.
Pour caramel over chocolate chips.
Crumble remaining cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Combine beans, onion and parsley in a large bowl.
Mix dressing, sugar and garlic; pour over bean mixture and toss. Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with grated sharp cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: sour cream apple pie(8 servings)
directions: Place slices of apples in pastry shell, overlapping.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Spread the cup of sour cream over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Really good!!

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Skin chicken breasts; cut off fat.
Wash thoroughly.
Place in a large pot.
Cover with water and boil until chicken is done. Remove chicken from bones.
Place back in broth on low heat; salt to taste.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: In a bowl, mix together the corn syrup, molasses, water, soda and egg.
Reserve about half of this mixture. To the rest, add the flour, butter and brown sugar.
Mix well and pour into pie crust. Carefully top with the reserved syrup and bake for 25 minutes at 400°. Allow to cool, then chill the pie before serving.

title: margie's spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cook awhile, then add vinegar and Lea & Perrins sauce.
Add soup and water, mix, then add rice.
Place rice mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake supreme(makes 3 layers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease three 9-inch cake pans, then cut wax paper to fit bottom.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Add 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup buttermilk, continuing until all is used, being sure to end with flour.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool to lukewarm and spread filling between layers and on top.

title: creole sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
This sauce is excellent on baked fish, veal or chicken.
One half gram of fat per serving and 28 calories.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Combine first 9 items (salt through butter) in a large casserole dish.
Add shrimp; stir.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350° (just until shrimp is pink).
Cook spaghetti and add with sliced cheese to shrimp mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three-in-one cheese ball
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce until mix is fluffy.
Divide into thirds (about 1 cup each).
Shape into balls and roll in cracked pepper. Add the Blue cheese to the second portion; mix well.
Shape into a ball; roll in parsley.
Add garlic powder to the remaining portion; mix well.
Shape into a ball; roll in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 3 cheese balls.

title: heavenly gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg and molasses.
Combine dry ingredients and mix slowly with wet.
Roll into teaspoon size balls.
Dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk cheese loaf
directions: Beat buttermilk, oil
and
eggs
with rotary egg beater until well blended.
In
a large bowl, combine dry ingredients with shredded cheese.
Add
egg mixture to dry ingredients and stir until just moist.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) and bake for 45 to
minutes
at
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then invert on rack until cool.

title: chicken with rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Put in rice (uncooked); mix this up so rice is greased.
Add chicken and sprinkle onion soup over top, then pour over top 1 can mushroom soup dissolved in 1 to 2 cans of water.
Place in 350° oven and bake, covered, until meat and rice are done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In large skillet thaw and separate broccoli in oil.
Blend in onions and cook for a short time.
Stir in soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Fold in rice and mix well.
Top with rest of cheese. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Wash and cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Sprinkle with onion salt and pepper. Place on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Grease sides of crock pot.
Mix all ingredients together and put into crock pot.
Cook 4-5 hours on slow (low) setting.
Can sprinkle top with parmesan cheese or sliced boiled eggs.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello and flour well.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix on medium speed.
Add pecans and strawberries; beat mixture well. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until done.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb with flour and sugar.
Dot with 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Pour in pastry-lined pan and top with crust which has slits cut in it.
Bake until brown at 400°, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dad's banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix.
Mix in flour, sour milk and bananas, alternate ingredients.

title: maple ham
directions: Cut off excess fat.
Stud the meat with cloves every inch or two.
Place in greased baking pan the same size as ham slice. Pour syrup over. Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for 1 hour or until meat is very tender.
Baste occasionally.
Easy.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and raisins for 10 minutes.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Continue cooking and stirring until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening and gradually add sugar.
Beat well at medium speed.
Add softened cream cheese, beating until fluffy.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Alternately add eggs and flour, beginning and ending with eggs.
Stir in vanilla.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: learning tree play dough
directions: Cook all ingredients together until mixture clumps together and turns translucent.
Turn onto cabinet and knead some flour into it.
Oil of cloves, peppermint or lemon may be added for fragrance.
This recipe keeps well and is good for a group of 4 to 6 children.

title: injero(flat bread)
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix the eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add this to the dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Pour 2 tablespoons of the batter into a hot, greased skillet.
Fry the batter like pancakes.
Drain each bread cake on a paper towel.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Serve warm.
Serves 24.

title: kentucky bourbon franks
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1/2-inch pieces and simmer in a large kettle with the remaining ingredients for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add a little more bourbon if sauce gets too dry. Do not cover.
Serve in chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, powder, salt, cinnamon, walnuts, and zucchini.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325 degrees for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain. Combine all ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into large bowl.
Chop cauliflower into lettuce. Place thinly sliced purple onion on top.
Sprinkle bacon bits into onion.
Mix Miracle Whip with sugar.
Whip up real good and spread onto top, being careful to seal in mixture.
Spread cheese on top. Now thinly cut up lettuce and spread on top of cheese.
Slice cauliflower thinly on top of lettuce.
Add purple onion slices and sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Seal with Saran wrap for 24 hours.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: Beat butter, salt and 1 cup of sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in chocolate, then add rest of sugar alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin frosting if needed for good spreading consistency.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with butter Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: cabbage hot tamales
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, chili powder, pepper and salt in balls (makes 10).
Wilt the cabbage leaves in boiling water.
Wrap.
Use toothpicks to hold.
Pour the tomatoes and 1 can water over it. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy banana pecan pie
directions: Combine flour, butter & pecans. Press into bottom and up sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Cool completely. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar. Fold in 1 C of whipped topping. Spread over crust. Arrange bananas on top. In a bowl, whisk pudding mix and milk. Immediately pour over bananas. Top with remaining whipped topping. Garnish with chopped pecans if desired. Refrigerate until serving.

title: java slush
directions: In blender container, blend all ingredients until smooth.

title: ever-so-easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine flour and baking soda in large bowl; combine remaining ingredients.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 to 50 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
Garnish as desired.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and Cool Whip together until smooth. Fold in other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, melt cheese in soup and stir occasionally.
Add pasta, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through, stirring carefully.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and baste your favorite grilled meats.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Broil ribs until brown and crisp on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Place in roaster or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onion in butter in 2-quart pan.
Add remaining ingredients and gently cook 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs in roaster.
Cover and bake at 375°.
After 45 minutes, turn ribs.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: pa dutch style chicken corn soup
directions: In large soup pot, fill enough water to cover bird.
Cook until chicken comes off the bones.
Remove from pot.
Add vegetables.
Season with garlic, salt, pepper, parsley, basil, thyme and sage.
Pick chicken off bones.
Throw out bones and skin.
Return meat to pot.
When vegetables are soft, add corn. Cook for another hour.
In small bowl, mix eggs and keep adding flour until it gets crusty, not doughy.
Break off little pieces of dough and drop in pot.
Cook about 1/2 hour.

title: old fashioned dressing
directions: Boil chicken.
Cook
all
seasoning,
onion
and celery with margarine for 10
to
minutes.	Add to crumb mixture. Combine milk, eggs and
meat from bony pieces of chicken;
add along with 1 1/4 cups	broth and toss lightly.
Bake in baking dish at 325° until firm.

title: old fashion tomato soup
directions: Bring tomatoes and water to boil.
Add butter.
Mix meal in small amount of cold water.
When meal dissolves, then add small amount of hot water.
Add to tomatoes. Add salt, pepper and sugar. Boil until tomatoes are well done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix everything together with your hands.
Mold it into a loaf and put it into an uncovered dish. Cook for 1 hour.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into large casserole bowl. Bake for about 40 minutes at 350°. Top with a can of French onion rings. (Cover to cook.)

title: pumpkin kasha(a russian dish pudding)
directions: Parboil rice, rinse in cold water and drain.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Pour mixture into two bowls about two quart size, which have been buttered.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for about 1 hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in Pyrex dish for 45 minutes.

title: rolled butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking powder and salt and sift again. Cream butter thoroughly. Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add vanilla and lemon juice, then add flour, mixing well. Chill until firm enough to roll. Roll 1/8-inch thick on slightly floured board. Cut with floured cutter. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 425° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *May use 1 can cream of mushroom and 1 can cream of chicken soups.

title: boxty(bacstai)
directions: Liquidise or grate potatoes.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Add milk to a dropping pancake consistency. Drop spoonfuls onto a hot, greased frying pan. Fry both sides.
Serve with hot butter. To prevent the batter from turning brown, do not leave the mixture stand but lightly fry and then re-fry before serving. Delicious with bacon rasher and fried egg.

title: pretzel jello ii
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Mix jello and hot juice.
Stir in berries.
Let partially set.
Spoon over other layers and refrigerate.
May use peach jello and fresh peaches.

title: texas chili
directions: Cook for 1 hour or so and serve with cheese and sour cream.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease large pie pan.
Place bacon, cheese and onion in pan.
Place rest of ingredients in blender and mix on high for 1 minute.
Pour over other ingredients and bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Can be halved.

title: caramel nut popcorn
directions: Toast pecans and almonds at 300° and cool.
Mix with popcorn. Mix sugar, butter, syrup and cream of tartar and cook until hard ball stage.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and then vanilla. Pour in popcorn.
Toss with buttered forks.
Press into cookie sheet.
Break up when cool.
Store in canister.

title: wild rice en consomme
directions: Wash rice under running water, then drain.
Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan or skillet.
Add onion, mushrooms and salt.
Cook until onion is tender; remove from heat.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole, stirring to mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done, stirring occasionally, while cooking.

title: jello punch
directions: Boil sugar and water to syrup.
Mix Jell-O according to directions.
Mix with pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice. Freeze into manageable quantities.

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in glass baking dish. Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning.
Slice tomato and lay on top of loaf.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: baked rice balls
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in a skillet.
Add tomato paste; stir and cook 5 minutes. Add water, salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix well and cool about 15 minutes.

title: old dominion cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch casserole.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; add milk and stir well.
Pour this mixture into casserole.
Top with fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and tomatoes. Combine dry ingredients together.
Gradually add to tomato mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country roast and vegetables
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Add peeled potatoes, carrots, green beans, corn, sliced onion and butter.
Add water and flour for gravy.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook on low for about 6 hours.
Cook on high for less than 6 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice the potatoes; cook in water until soft. Cut fat meat in tiny pieces and fry. Add sliced onions and fry until brown.
Pour into the kettle with the potatoes. Mix sour cream with well beaten egg.
Pour into the potatoes and onions. Stir well. Add enough vinegar to give it a sour taste.
Let all come to a good boil. Serve hot.

title: hot italian sausage
directions: Place Sausages in Water bringing to a boil and simmer until the sausages are firm. Remove the sausage,
being careful not to pierce them when taking them out (this could add unwanted fat to the soup). Cut the sausage into bite-size pieces and return to the water.

title: depot cherry cobbler
directions: In 325° oven melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, mix flour and sugar and stir in milk until blended.
When margarine is melted, remove from oven and pour batter onto margarine.
Do not stir.
Gently spoon pie filling into batter.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: orange rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix like biscuits.
Grease bowl and top of dough.
Let rise in refrigerator.
Roll out dough.
Cover with orange marmalade.
Roll like jelly roll.
Slice.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° to 425° until lightly browned.
While hot, brush with orange juice-confectioners sugar mixture.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions on package.
Blend cream cheese until smooth; add to pudding.
Add powdered sugar to mixture; fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Use a large clean, new flowerpot; put a piece of foil over the bottom. Sprinkle some cookie crumbs on the bottom.
Add a layer of cream cheese filling; continue layers of cookies and filling, ending with cookie crumbs on top.
Place a bunch of artificial flowers in center of pot for realistic look.
You can also put candy gummy worms on top.

title: beef stew
directions: In a large pot cook stew meat, onions, salt and pepper until beef is very tender (about two hours). Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: chocolate kisses
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, salt and butter; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: colorful corn salad
directions: Stir together corn and next 6 ingredients in a bowl until thoroughly mixed. Cover and chill 2 hours. Serve salad with a slotted spoon. Top each serving with chopped cucumber, if desired. Makes 5 cups.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Mix well, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: frozen gold corn
directions: Mix sugar, salt and water.
Bring to boil, add corn and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pack in containers and freeze.

title: mexican pie
directions: Cook ground beef and drain fat.
Return meat to skillet; add onion, green pepper, sauce and seasonings and simmer.
Cook corn or mixed vegetables according to instructions, until tender.
Mix with meat sauce and season to taste if further is needed.
Prepare Jiffy mix as instructed on the box.
Place meat sauce and vegetables that have been mixed into a casserole dish and pour Jiffy mix on top. Cook at 350° until golden brown.
If oven cooks fast, reduce heat to ensure Jiffy mix is completely cooked.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain in thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger and toss.
Marinate beef 1/2 hour.
Heat oil in wok; add beef and toss over high heat until brown.
Simmer 30 or 40 minutes, covered.
Turn heat up and add vegetables; toss until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan and stir and cook until thick.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: 24 hour tossed salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces; then layer lettuce with rest of veggies, except peas, in large bowl.
Then spread all the peas.
Next spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle sugar over all. Sprinkle bacon chips and grated cheese over all.
Cover tight and let sit overnight.
Toss well before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in broth.
Melt butter.
Add chopped onion and garlic; let cook until limp.
Add it and other ingredients to spaghetti except peas and cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir often and cook slowly as it sticks easily.
Add peas.
Before serving, sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: forman's salt-rising bread
directions: While getting breakfast in the morning, as soon as the tea kettle has boiled, take a quart tin cup or an earthen quart milk pitcher, scald it, then fill one third full of water about as warm as the finger can be held in it, then to this add salt, brown sugar and coarse flour (enough to make a batter of about the right consistency for griddle cakes).
Set the cup, with the spoon in it, in a closed vessel half filled with water moderately hot, but not scalding.
Keep that temperature as nearly even as possible and add a teaspoon of flour once or twice during the process of fermentation.

title: skillet taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 10 or 11-inch ovenproof skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning mix and tomato sauce to browned beef.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spread mixture in skillet; remove from heat.
In bowl, blend biscuit mix and milk. On floured surface pat dough to form a circle 1 inch smaller than skillet.
Transfer dough to top of browned beef.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Place large platter upside down on skillet.
Turn over to transfer taco pie on platter.
Sprinkle cheese over beef mixture; distribute lettuce on top of cheese.
Put tomatoes on center of cheese.
Make 6 dollops of sour cream on pie.
Cut into 6 wedges.

title: nancy's crab pate
directions: Heat soup, dissolve gelatin in cold water, add gelatin to soup, stirring well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spoon into oiled 4-cup mold (preferably a fish mold).
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating very well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to mixture.
Mix well; add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil or spray with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove cookies from sheet while still warm.
Yields: 36 cookies.
One cookie equals 89 calories.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix cheese and other ingredients together until blended.
Spread on bread.
Place under broiler and cook until brown and bubbly.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Combine oil and sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I use four 7 x 3 1/2-inch pans and bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: sinful brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Next....

title: rice dressing supreme
directions: Heat chicken broth to boiling point; season with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Add the rice and stir until it boils up once; lower flame, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Saute the onions and celery in margarine until clear.
Add mushrooms and seasonings and combine with rice when it has finished steaming.
Serve very hot.

title: port wine jello
directions: After dissolving jello, mix rest of ingredients and place in refrigerator until set.
Can be placed in mold.

title: whipped butter
directions: Allow
butter
to
soften at room temperature.
Combine nonfat dry
milk and water.
Add reconstituted milk to soften butter
in mixer bowl.
Blend on low speed, then whip on high speed.
Yields 98 (2 1/2 teaspoon) portions.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar, then gradually add eggs. Gradually add flour, buttermilk and soda. Add vanilla, coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° in greased and flour pans (2 layers of 9 x 13-inch) 25 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole(this is an unusual, but delicious casserole.)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool to room temperature, then freeze in Baggies.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mash potato; add salt, yeast, shortening, water and sugar until dissolved.
Add to flour; knead.
Shape into ball.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise double size.
Punch down.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar; mix and let rise again.
Roll out dough and spread with butter, white sugar, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Roll up; cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place in pan.
Let rise.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: catfish house mix
directions: Quarter tomatoes and onions.
Mix all ingredients together. Bring to a boil or until the tomatoes turn light green; do not boil. Gently stir
a couple of times. Seal in hot jars.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until well blended. Add egg and beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Mix until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Remove cookies to foil to cool.

title: mud pie
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mushrooms marsala in brioche
directions: Saute mushrooms, green onions (finely chopped, including part of the green tops), tarragon, salt and pepper in butter.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Add wine and blend well.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Add ham, cut in julienne pieces and whipping cream and remove from heat when warm.
Remove top hats from brioches and scoop out some of the soft center.
Brush the inside of each brioche and the bottom of the "top hat" with melted butter.
Place in a baking pan and divide the mushroom mixture between the brioches.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle the top hats with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Replace top hats before serving.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Put pineapple into a baking dish.
Pat bread pieces over pineapple.
Mix eggs, sugar and butter; beat until light and fluffy.
Add 1/2 the pineapple juice to the egg mixture.
Pour over top of bread pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken pecan log
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Stir in chicken and celery.
Shape into a log; chill 4 hours or overnight. Coat with pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Mix jello with hot water and add with flavoring to cake. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in tube pan.

title: divinity swirls
directions: Blend sugar, corn syrup and water in medium sized saucepan. Cook over high heat, without stirring, until a teaspoon of syrup dropped in cold water forms a soft ball; remove from heat.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
Pour 1/3 syrup on egg whites.
Cook remaining syrup fast over high heat until a teaspoon dropped into cold water forms a hard ball.
Pour in fine steam over egg white mixture, beating constantly.
Add vanilla; continue to beat until candy is very stiff and forms peaks that do not flatten out.
Swirl on wax paper.

title: esther's green bean casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and cream of celery soup and pour over casserole.
Melt margarine and Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt fat; add onions and fry.
Add meat and cook until browned.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes. Serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Check at about an hour for doneness.

title: barbecued rice
directions: In heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Add celery and onion; cook until clear.
Add chicken soup and broth, liquid smoke, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into a casserole dish; add rice and garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, sugar, salt and seasonings.
In small bowl, combine milk and eggs thoroughly. Blend in molasses and oil.
Pour batter into 2 greased square baking pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown. Remove pans.
Use toothpick to test for doneness.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 9 to 10.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add all eggs at one time. Add milk, coconut, nuts, baking powder and vanilla. Add cracker crumbs. Bake two layers at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream together
eggs,
oil,
sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add milk, flour, soda and
baking powder.
Add bran and raisins. Don't stir much after adding flour.
Bake
at
for 15 minutes.
Makes 24.
Can be mixed ahead and stored in refrigerator until used.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour, one cup at a time.
Add oatmeal, one cup at a time.
Mixture will be very thick.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly, then add the cream.
Beat until smooth.

title: gazpacho(a delicious cold soup or appetizer.)
directions: * They peel easier when dipped in boiling water first for a few seconds, then in ice or cold water; do not overcook! I've also not peeled tomatoes and it still tastes great!

title: oatmeal chewies
directions: Cream together Crisco, granular sugar and brown sugar; add 2 well beaten eggs, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Then add flour, blended with soda and salt; mix together.
Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
You may immediately bake these cookies by dropping them onto the cookie sheet, or they can be rolled in wax paper and chilled.
(If chilled, slice 1/4-inch thick and place on cookie sheet.)
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
If you like chewy cookies, don't let them overcook.
If you like crunchy cookies, let them brown.

title: glazed country baked ham
directions: Soak country ham overnight.
Take ham and trim off excess fat. Then cut diagonally across whole ham.
Heat honey and brown sugar in the microwave until the mixture gets soft and spreadable.
Pour the mixture over ham.
Put ham in deep pan half full of water and put in a 375° oven for 3 to 4 hours or until ham pulls away from the bone.

title: vegetable ball (dip)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball.
Roll mixture in chopped pecans (about 3/4 cup).
Great with Ritz crackers.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and peanut butter; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes or until firm.
Meanwhile, melt the white coating in a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt and blend thoroughly.
Stir in the scalded milk.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture thickens. Continue to cook about 2 minutes.
Pour some of the mixture over the slightly beaten egg yolk.
Cook for 1 minute longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook, pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: sausage bites(catherine hamilton's kitchen)
directions: Mix
ingredients
together well.
Roll into balls, size of quarter
(approximately).
Put
onto cookie sheet.	Bake at 350° for
10 minutes, approximately or until lightly browned. Serve hot.
Great for guests.

title: cheddar or mozzarella cheese bread
directions: Thaw the white bread; spread it out.
Put cheese, garlic and onion evenly over the bread.
Roll it up.
Butter the top; sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon asparagus pilaf
directions: Melt butter and oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, cook, stirring 5 minutes.
Stir in asparagus, thyme, salt and pepper and cook for 1 minute.
Add rice, stir for 1 minute. Add broth and water; cover and bring to a simmer.
Reduce heat and cook until rice is done and asparagus is tender, about 25-30 minutes.
Stir in zest and lemon juice just before serving.

title: caramel squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
It will be dry; press the mixture in bottom of a lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Form into walnut size meatballs.
Arrange in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.

title: quick and easy pizzas
directions: Spoon desired amount of sauce onto pita bread.
Add your choice of toppings.
Top with cheese.
Place on cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Kids love them!

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast
with
warm water.
Add sugar and Crisco. Mix in flour.
Let
rise
until double in size. Work down and make out into rolls.
Then cover with melted margarine and let rise to double
(about
hours).
Bake
in a 350° oven until done.

title: vegetable soup(for freezing)
directions: In a large pot, add tomatoes, juice and carrots.
Cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients, except peas.
Bring to a boil and cook vegetables until tender.
Add peas and simmer.
May need to add more juice or water.
Flavor as desired, salt, pepper, sugar, beef or chicken bouillon. This makes a thick soup.
I freeze in serving size containers.
When opened, add beef or chicken broth if desired, water or V-8 juice.
Heat and serve.

title: sausage-cabbage-potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer sliced potatoes and chopped onion.
Shred cabbage and put on top.
Mix cream of celery soup with 1 can of water and pour on top of cabbage.
Cut sausage in chunks and arrange on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rita's famous salad
directions: Wisk ingredients together until mixed well and chill.

title: slush punch(serves 100 people, 8 ounce cups)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and cold water.
Then freeze overnight or 6 to 12 hours.
Remove, shake and add 7-Up or one of the other. Delicious. Great for weddings or showers, just any time.
Freeze in punch bowl.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead vigorously and long.
After a few minutes, it should form a ball that holds together.
If sticky, add flour, a handful at a time.
If too dry and stiff, add skim milk.
Use either a kneader pot or by hand on a floured board.

title: choc-peanut butter fudge
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, salt, milk, butter and vanilla. Stir.
Bring to a boil about 4 minutes until it becomes a soft ball. Add peanut butter until it starts to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan. Chill for 1 hour.

title: instant cucumber pickles
directions: Using a quart jar or plastic container, layer onions and cucumber slices.
Pour vinegar mixture over slices.
Cover.
Keep in refrigerator.
Pickles will keep for several months.
These are similar to bread and butter pickles.

title: cheese danish
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix with electric mixer on high until creamy, about 3 minutes; set aside.
Unroll 1 package crescent roll dough evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing down to close perforations.
Spread cheese mixture evenly on dough.
Unroll other package dough evenly over filling.
Whip egg whites in small bowl until frothy; spread evenly atop dough.
Sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool, cut into bars.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion and garlic until hamburger is light brown; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 1 hour.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 1 1/4 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of a 10 x 15 pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before adding filling.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Set jello.
Add whole cranberry sauce, pineapple, chopped apple, celery and nuts.
Stir as thickens.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites and gradually beat in sugar and lemon extract. Bake at 350° until browned a little.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick fix burritos
directions: Place burritos in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce and salsa over burritos.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice several apples into bottom of 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Cover with mixture of sugar, flour and oatmeal.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Should be crispy when done.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Slice angel food cake and line pan or dish.
Beat remaining ingredients with a mixer.
Layer mixture over cake, then put another layer of cake, followed by another layer of remaining mixture.
Cover with 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: tom thumb bars
directions: Cream the shortening, salt and brown sugar. Add the flour and blend.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix the above together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with any fruit pie filling.

title: hot chicken-cheese heroes
directions: In medium
bowl,
toss chicken and celery with almonds, onion, lemon
juice, pepper, salt and mayonnaise.	Cut off top of each roll;
then scoop out center.
Fill rolls with chicken mixture. Arrange
rolls
in	baking	pan;
sprinkle tops with grated cheese.
Bake
about
25 minutes or until cheese begins to bubble. Serves 4.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Add cornstarch and sugar together in a large saucepan.
Mix in 1 cup water.
Cook over low flame until thick.
Add lemon juice and margarine, then add pineapple and rhubarb.
Put in 10-inch deep crust and cover with top crust.
Make a slit in center for steam to escape.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: granola bark
directions: Melt candy in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add granola; mix until well blended.
Turn out on cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Cover top with another sheet of waxed paper; roll flat with a rolling pin.
Place in refrigerator until set, then break into pieces.

title: apple cinnamon crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend dry cake mix, oil and eggs.
Drop from a teaspoon about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip the bottom of a glass in mixture and press each cookie flat (dip glass bottom for each cookie). Press a nut half on center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until medium brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute. Remove to racks for further cooling.
Store tightly covered. Yield:
5 to 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into 1 gallon container.
Add enough water to fill container.
Shake well.
Freeze until ready to use.
Thaw until the texture of slush.
