Serve immediately. Yield:
1 gallon.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add salt and pepper.
Drain and set aside.
Mix soups, Pet milk, taco sauce and cheese.
Tear flour tortillas into pieces.
Layer tortillas in bottom of casserole. Add meat and sauce.
Put cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cover with foil.

title: microwave honeyed onions
directions: Place onions in 1-quart glass baking dish.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes; drain. Stir in margarine and honey; cover.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes longer.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes before serving.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown hamburg (loose).
Add onion soup and water (as desired). Add spaghetti (as desired).
Allow to cook and thicken with cornstarch.

title: cheesy chicken broccoli macaroni
directions: Spray large skillet with cooking spray.
Cook and stir chicken in large skillet.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, peanut butter and water together.
Roll into small balls (about 1/2 teaspoon).
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 5 to 10 minutes; remove from oven and press chocolate chip into center of hot cookie.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together and drop from a tablespoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: lasagne 2
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste, simmering 45 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain. Rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs and seasonings.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread half the cottage cheese sauce, half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then cut in squares.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, cocoa and margarine.
Add vanilla, milk and water; beat until mixed well.
Pour into a glass dish and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Let set about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°.
Cook for 35 minutes.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, beaten egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients in order written.
Spoon on baking sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup butter. Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil. Remove.
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture and beat well. Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and Eagle Brand.
Stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with all ingredients except pie shell, blending well with electric mixer (or hand mix using a wooden spoon).
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 30 minutes, or until golden and puffy.
Serve alone or topped with whipped cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9x9 pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour over melted butter. Do not stir.
Drop peaches into mixture.
Do not stir. Bake at 325 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Cook eggs, flour, sugar and juice together until thick. Let cool, then beat in mayonnaise.
Add crushed, drained pineapple. Makes 2 pints and will keep in refrigerator for days.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except pastry shell; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk, vinegar and corn syrup in a saucepan and boil for 6 minutes.
Pour this mixture over peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until thick, then pour into greased pans.
When cool, cut into desired size pieces.
Makes about 5 pounds of fudge.

title: apple crisp
directions: Blend all ingredients except apples and melted butter with fork.
Arrange sliced apples in 8 x 8-inch lightly greased square pan.
Spread mixture over apples.
Extra cinnamon and sugar may be sprinkled over mixture.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm, great with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs and cooled margarine with two sugars.
Blend very well.
Add flour and pecans to mixture, again blend well.
Layer 1/2 cup chocolate chips onto bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over chocolate chips until it reaches top of 10-inch pie tin.
Place in preheated oven.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together to make the dip.
If using hard cream cheese, let it get to room temperature and knead in package before adding.
Pour dip into large platter, then layer on the ingredients you are using, for example dip, lettuce, tomatoes and then cheese.
You can add or delete anything you like.
Use chips for dipping.
Always a huge success, even with the kids.

title: toffee
directions: In heavy pan, melt butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 290° on candy thermometer.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet covered with the nuts.
Spread out as thin as you can.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top.
When melted, spread to make icing.
Let cool completely.

title: pear under the sea salad
directions: Dice pears; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add reserved syrup and lemon juice.
Pour 1 1/4 cups into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 1 hour.

title: apple cobbler superb
directions: Pare and core apples; slice thin.
Drop apple slices into maple syrup; stir to coat apples.
Spread evenly in greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cream butter to consistency of mayonnaise.
Add sugar while continuing to cream.
Beat in egg. Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to butter and sugar mixture.
Spoon over apples, spreading smoothly with rubber spatula.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until topping is golden brown and cake tester comes out clean. May be served warm with plain cream and additional maple syrup, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix hot water and margarine in a bowl. Stir in stuffing mix, pepper and half of the pineapple and syrup. Spoon evenly on chicken and roll.
Secure with toothpicks.
Put in square pan with remaining stuffing in center.
Mix remaining pineapple, syrup, sugar, vinegar and ginger.
Spoon over chicken. Bake 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, and salt in large bowl.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans, drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Serve with whipped topping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Wash the vegetables and cut them into small pieces.
Put the vegetable oil into a saucepan.
Add the onions and fry for 2 minutes.
Add the tomato sauce, peppers and salt.
Leave it on a medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add the vegetables and 2 cups of water and let simmer until soft and tender.
Do not overcook the vegetables.
Serve with fried rice plantain or cooked rice.

title: the all-american (turkey) burger
directions: Mix all the ingredients and form into 4 patties; grill indoors or out on the barbecue.
Serve on the proverbial toasted bun or choose sourdough bread for less fat and cholesterol.
Pile high with lettuce, tomato slices and onion rings grilled on a no stick pan sprayed with Pam.
Serves 4.

title: janet's punch
directions: Mix and freeze the first 3 ingredients in mold.
Add ginger ale.

title: peach delight
directions: Blend cream soda, vanilla extract, ice cubes and sweetener until mixed well, then add Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplements and blend to desired consistency.
Um-um good!

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine all ingredients, except nuts and chocolate chips, in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well at lowest speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Cook eggs, milk and 1 cup sugar in double boiler until mixture coats the spoon.
Then add remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar, Carnation milk and vanilla.
Mix with cooked mixture.
Add enough milk to make 1 gallon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pour into 1 gallon ice cream freezer and freeze as directed.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables. Mix the sugar, vinegar, oil and salt together and bring to a boil. Add to vegetables and chill overnight. (Will keep for a week.)

title: mama's chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in big pot and add salt. Make up dumplings like you would biscuits, except use only flour and cold water. Roll dough out thin and cut in little pieces; drop in boiling water with chicken. Sprinkle black pepper and cook until dumplings are done.

title: peas and new potatoes
directions: Pull strings from peas.
Place in a 6-quart kettle. Cover with water. Cook while you are cleaning the potatoes.
Use a brush and brush off all loose peelings.
Place on top of peas. Add bacon grease and cook until peas are tender and most of the liquid is absorbed, on medium heat about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend sugar and margarine together, then eggs and then mix dry ingredients.
Place in a greased bread pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: In 3-quart pan, saute onion in margarine until translucent. Sprinkle flour, mustard, salt and pepper, continuing to stir vigorously.
Slowly stir in milk, continuously stirring until mixture boils; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; blend in grated cheese.
Drain macaroni well and add to the sauce.
Spray large baking dish with Pam; add mixture.
Mix bread crumbs with paprika; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour until toothpick comes clean.
Use 2 greased and floured pans.

title: toads in a hole(great for psyching out your kids!)
directions: Cook sausage and save drippings (10 minutes).
Sift flour and salt in a bowl.
Make well in center and add half the milk and 2 eggs, well beaten.
Gradually mix flour in liquid.
At end, add rest of milk.
Beat vigorously.
Pour batter in with mushrooms and sausage.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes until golden.
The sausages are "toad" and the mushrooms are the "toadstools".
Fun for Halloween.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple juice in pan.
Add grated cheese and sugar. Add flour.
Mix together and pour over pineapple. Add 3/4 pack Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: cornmeal crust pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugars and pumpkin pie spice in small bowl. Beat eggs in large bowl. Stir in pumpkin and sugar and spice mixture. Gradually stir in evaporated milk. Pour into pie shell that has been sprayed with Pam and covered with cornmeal on bottom and all sides. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 2 hours. Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: chili con cornbread(very quick and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour chili into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in order listed.
Blend well.
Pour batter over chili.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with salad or slaw.

title: tuna-pasta salad in tomato cups
directions: With a sharp knife, cut off and reserve a thick slice from the blossom end of each tomato.
Scoop out tomato pulp and seeds. Leave tomato, cut side down, on paper to dry for 5 minutes. Coarsely chop tomato pulp.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions 5 minutes.
Drain well. Add other ingredients and salt to taste.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Slit squash and boil in salted water until tender.
Remove and run fork down pulp in squash.
Mix Cavender's seasoning with sour cream and spread over each squash and sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and corn starch. Cook over low heat stirring as cooking until thick. Add Jell-o. Stir until mixed. Remove from heat and let cool. While still warm, add berries. Mix and pour into baked pie crust. Refrigerate until set and cool. Top with Cool Whip.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion (drain grease).
Add corn, soups, pimento, sour cream and seasonings.
Cook noodles and drain. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Mix together crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat, then add onion and celery and cook until tender. Add spaghetti, tomatoes and vegetables and place in casserole dish.
Cover top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly, 5 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix browned hamburger with taco seasoning, beans and sour cream.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Add cheese and put back into oven to melt.
Serve warm with nacho-style chips.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Brown onion and celery together until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 10 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Contains 75 calories per 8 ounce serving.
Can add mushrooms and hamburger for variations.

title: pumpkin gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pan or 3 (5 1/2 x 3-inch) pans.
Into bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, ginger, salt and cloves.
In another bowl, combine pumpkin, egg, milk and oil; blend well.
Add flour mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in crystallized ginger.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes on wire rack.
Serve warm or cool completely.

title: pinto bean, sausage and fennel gratin
directions: In a kettle combine the beans with enough cold water to cover them by 2-inches and simmer them, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until they are tender.
Drain the beans in a colander set over a large bowl and reserve the cooking liquid.
In a large heavy skillet, cook the sausage over moderate heat, stirring and breaking up any lumps, until it is cooked through and transfer it with a slotted spoon to a bowl.

To the fat remaining in the skillet, add the oil and in the fat cook the onion, fennel, bell pepper, basil, thyme, salt and pepper to taste over moderate heat, stirring until the vegetables are softened.
Add the broth and simmer the mixture, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix and bake the cake mix according to directions on package. Remove cake from oven and immediately poke cake full of holes with a two tined meat fork.
Spread the pineapple over the cake.
Cool cake.
Mix the pudding and cook and top over cake.
Let cake stand overnight, if possible.
One hour before serving, top it off with the Cool Whip.

title: banana bread(yield: 1 loaf)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: aunt kitty pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in 10-inch glass pie plate.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg and milk together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to milk mixture.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour batter over melted margarine in pie plate.
Drop cooked apples by spoonfuls over dough.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown. I also use cooked green apples.

title: mom's liver
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain, saving the grease.
Mix flour, thyme and seasoning salt in bowl.
Cut liver in 1/2-inch strips.
Dip the liver in lemon juice, coat with flour mixture. Fry in bacon grease, (add a little cooking oil if needed) until done.
Sprinkle top of liver with chopped onions and crumbled bacon.
Serve.

title: baked rice pilaf
directions: Combine rice, soup, water, water chestnuts and butter.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, in oven preheated to 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cashew chicken and snow peas
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips and season with salt and pepper. Remove stems and strings from snow peas and cut in half diagonally if very large.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in wok or large skillet; add chicken and stir-fry over high heat until just cooked through, about 2 to 3 minutes; remove to plate.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to wok and stir-fry peas over high heat for 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium and add garlic and cashews.	Cook while stirring for 1 minute.
Return chicken to pan and add chicken broth; simmer about 1 minute until heated through.	Serves 4.

title: great-grandma's zucchini bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: raisin pie
directions: Add raisins to water.
Simmer until tender (3 to 5 minutes). Combine sugars, cornstarch and salt; stir into hot raisins.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, to full rolling boil; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Blend in fruit rinds and juices.
Pour hot filling into pastry-lined pie pan; dot top with butter.
Cover with remaining pastry.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve slightly warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine finely diced rhubarb and sugar; let set for 3 hours. Then add flour and eggs (beaten).
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.
Use knife to test center.
When knife comes out clean, it's done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat well.
Add apples and nuts.
Blend.
The mixture will be very thick.
Turn into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until done when tested.
Blend lemon juice with xxx sugar until smooth.
Spread over warm cake.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: date nut bars
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and light brown sugar.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well and add dates and walnuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet pan.

title: hot sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: "bride's chicken"
directions: Place flour, paprika and pepper in plastic bag.
Shake chicken cutlets in bag (a few at a time) until coated thoroughly.
Fry in butter and oil until golden brown.
Place cutlets in a shallow baking or roasting pan.

title: sauteed zucchini and sausage
directions: Cook sausage in a small skillet until browned; drain off drippings, reserving 1 1/2 tablespoons.
Crumble sausage and return it to the skillet.
Add zucchini and onion to sausage.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in tomato sauce, cook until thoroughly heated.
Place mixture in a serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 2.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 11 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, margarine, water and 1 egg.
Press into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Blend together the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar; pour onto top of cake mix layer.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: orange cake
directions: Drain 1 can of oranges and add to cake mix along with orange extract and add eggs, oil and water as directed on box.
Beat together and pour into a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake and cool as directed on box.
Top with whipped cream to which the other can of drained and chopped
oranges
have been added.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: teriyaki chicken bits
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce and sugar in small bowl.
Add chicken and marinate 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken; reserve 2 tablespoons of marinade.
Combine reserved marinade, water and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat oil in hot wok or skillet over medium heat.
Stir-fry chicken and sesame seed for 2 minutes. Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens and chicken is tender, about 1 minute.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together pumpkin, cooking oil, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
After these ingredients are mixed, add flour, baking soda and baking powder gradually and then mix good.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: aunt nancy's dressing(for macaroni or potato salad)
directions: Beat eggs in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to eggs. Add vinegar; beat.
Cook until thick.
Add salad dressing and mustard.
Cool.
Pour over ingredients for potato salad or cooked macaroni and pickles.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: In a large 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, mix pie filling, sugar and vanilla.
Spread evenly.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over pie mixture.
Cover with melted oleo.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: pineapple-orange marmalade
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into pan.
Sprinkle gelatin on juice.
Wait 1 minute, until soft.
Then heat gently until gelatin melts.
Remove from heat and stir in pineapple and thawed orange juice and sweetener.
Store in covered jars in refrigerator.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix together cake mixes, eggs and butter (softened).
Add club soda and whiskey.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in tube pan in preheated 350° oven for 70 minutes.
Let cool and remove from pan.
Mmmmm good!

title: orange date bars
directions: Add 3 tablespoons hot water.
Spoon about 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with date mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and 1 cup chopped orange slices over all, then spread the rest of batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Cut crust from 12 slices of bread.
Butter 6 and line a 9 x 13 casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on top of the bread in casserole.
Cover with 6 slices bread and top with mixture of sour cream and chicken soup.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
This may be made a day ahead of time.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mrs. tuttle's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Add sugar and fat to sweet potatoes while hot.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with potato mixture. Knead for 1 minute.
Pat to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with hot butter.

title: molded orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Stir in orange sherbet while mixture is still warm.
Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple, reserving liquid.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups combined liquid. Add oranges and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate all day for serving at dinner.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, chocolate and milk until a soft ball forms in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat until thick and pour into buttered dish.

title: stroganoff bread
directions: Cut French bread in half.
Toast at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes. Brown meat with green onion.
Stir in sour cream.
Mix in milk, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Heat mixture, but do not boil.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Assemble doughmaker.
In small mixer bowl, combine egg, shortening, sugar, milk and bran.
Mix, using doughmaker setting on #12.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquid mixture.
Mix with doughmaker just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deluxe sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract thoroughly.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar. Cover; chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Mix in partially thawed potatoes, sour cream, soup, cheese and salt. Top casserole with 2 cups crushed corn flakes. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made a day ahead, reserving the corn flakes until ready to bake.
Serves 16.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between wax paper or plastic wrap and pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add chives or green onions, lime juice, brandy, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15
seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth; stir until smooth.
Whisk remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: toasted pecan pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, combine butter, coconut, flour pecans and sugar.
Spread into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Meanwhile, in a large mixing bowl, beat pudding and milk on low speed for 2 minutes.
Chill for 5 minutes. Fold in the whipped topping.
Place half of the pecan mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Spread pudding mixture over pecan mixture.
Top with remaining pecan mixture.
Chill until serving. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: plan ahead party punch(good for large groups)
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar with water. Add lemonade (full strength), orange juice (full strength) and ginger ale.
(Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated.)
To serve, can add ice ring or ice cubes made with same liquid.

title: corn tomato chowder
directions: Cut pork into small pieces and fry slowly to a golden brown in a large saucepan.
Add onion and cook slowly without browning for 5 minutes.
Add corn, potatoes and tomatoes in alternate layers. Sprinkle with salt, sugar and pepper.
Then add water and cook slowly until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat and stir milk in slowly.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a food processor.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until light brown. Mix next 6 ingredients in a food processor.
Pour over hot crust.
Continue to bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute butter, onion and pepper.
Add chicken breasts; saute. Add sliced smoked sausage; saute.
Add Ro-Tel, tomatoes and rice. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Mix with salt, pepper, and paprika. Marinate over night and mix occasionally. Can add 15 oz. can garbanzo beans.
1/2 c. = 75 calories. Can use sugar substitute.
*Evelyn used this from the time she became diabetic.

title: tuna fritters
directions: Blend biscuit mix, seasoned salt, egg, milk and lemon juice in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Drop from teaspoon into deep fat at 375° or into 1/2-inch hot fat in frying pan.
Fry from 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on each side.
Serves 5.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: Layer cheeses and peppers in a baking dish.
Beat eggs, add flour, milk, and salt.
Pour over cheese and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is brown.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: any time of year pickles
directions: Drain dills.
Slice pickles 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and replace in jar.
Add sugar, cinnamon and onion.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, changing position up and down.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Slice kielbasa diagonally into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place the sauerkraut in a colander and rinse briefly under cold running water, then squeeze it dry with your hands.
Heat the oil in a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the kielbasa and stir until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to paper towel to drain.

Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat from pan. Add onions and reduce heat to medium; saute, stirring constantly, until the onions are wilted and golden brown, about 5 minutes. Add the sauerkraut and stir evenly.
Stir the chicken broth, mustard and cloves together in a small bowl.
Add the broth mixture to the skillet and stir well.
Arrange half of the sauerkraut mixture in bottom of a 12-inch casserole dish.
Place slices of kielbasa, overlapping in a layer on top of sauerkraut. Top with remaining kraut.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and potatoes in a bowl.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Melt butter and margarine in milk over low heat and add to sugar mixture.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and half of flour. Beat eggs and add to remaining flour.
Combine the two mixtures and mix well.
Let rise 1 hour.
Stir down and place in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, melt more butter and dip small, elongated rolls of dough in it.
Place rolls of dough in well-buttered ring mold, making only two layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When serving, tear off bread with fingers instead of cutting.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 6 ingredients. Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Add dry ingredients and margarine; mix only until flour is moistened. Stir in nuts.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix crushed Ritz crackers with the melted oleo.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: tomato wedge salad(serves 8)
directions: In a glass dish, place tomatoes and marinate in half the salad dressing; stir often.
Chill.
In another bowl, place lima beans and remaining dressing.
Chill.

title: snicker brownies
directions: Combine 1/3 cup evaporated milk and caramels over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk, melted butter, nuts and cake mix.
Stir with spoon.
Put 1/2 cake mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture and spread caramels over chips. Spoon remaining cake mixture over caramels and bake at 350° for 15 minutes longer.
Cool in refrigerator. Cut in squares.

title: top of stove cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in pan; bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; drop on wax paper.
Raisins, nuts or coconut may be added.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix with 1/2 can (5 ounces) evaporated milk.
Add 3/4 cup soft butter.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 12-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crumble Oreo
cookies
in
bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Save a few
for topping.	Mix pudding mix according to directions on the
package.
Mix together pudding mix with whipped cream cheese, then
add	Cool
Whip on top.
Sprinkle crushed Oreo cookies on top.

title: pineapple punch (pink)
directions: Soften sherbet slightly in punch bowl.
Slowly add chilled cranberry juice and ginger ale.
Serves 40.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crush potato chips and spread on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marguerite's clam casserole
directions: As delicious as it is easy, it's almost a souffle.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in a casserole and swirl it around to coat well.
In a mixing bowl, combine minced clams with juice, dill weed, saltines, eggs which have been beaten and combined with 2 cups of milk and pepper to taste.
Mix together and place in casserole.
Sprinkle well with paprika. Let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 350° or until well set.
Serves 4.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make four 1-inch thick beef patties.
Place on individual pieces of aluminum foil.
Salt and pepper patties, then top with remaining ingredients.
Tightly seal foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato fans
directions: Cut potatoes crosswise into 1/4-inch slices, taking care not to cut through bottom.
Place cut side up, in a shallow pan. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Brush potatoes with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender and slices have fanned out.
Baste occasionally with pan drippings while baking. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips over double boiler and stir in condensed milk.
While hot, spread over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour or more.
Cut into squares or fingers.

title: maple-pecan carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water and salt to a boil.
Add carrots; cover and cook over medium heat for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain; cover to keep warm.
Melt butter in pan on low heat; stir in syrup.
Add carrots.
Cook until carrots are well glazed, stirring constantly.
Serve, topped with pecans. Makes 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: super easy fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat, stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into a wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 or 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except green onion tops.
Refrigerate about 4 hours.
Roll in green tops of onions.
Serve with crackers.

title: mayonnaise corn bread
directions: Combine pancake mix, corn meal and salt.
Stir in egg and mayonnaise.
Add enough water to make batter.
Pour into oiled 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
This is terrific!

title: mexican hot dish!!
directions: Mix in large bowl the chili, beans, onion, soup, green chilies and milk.
Spray casserole liberally with Pam.
Place layer of broken pieces of tortilla chips in bottom of pan and spoon meat mixture over.
Continue layering chips and meat mixture, ending with topping of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be divided and frozen for future use.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Place chicken in saucepan.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and peppercorns.
Mix well.
Add bay leaf and vinegar.
Cook over high heat until liquid comes to a fast boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and let simmer until chicken is tender and liquid has evaporated.
Add oil and brown.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add cake flour and salt.
Beat well after each cup of flour is added.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
May be glazed or frosted, but good by itself.
Velvety and delicious.

title: heath bars
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Lay the crackers, side by side, on the foil.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar and margarine. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over crackers and immediately sprinkle on chocolate chips. Spread chocolate over crackers with spatula as chips melt.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts and let cool.
Once cooled, remove from foil and break into pieces.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add oil and beat.
Add sugar and beat; stir in vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Fold in cake mixture and add chopped apples and nuts.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.
Makes 2 (8-inch) loaves or use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate-caramel poke and pour cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk into holes.
Pour ice cream topping over the milk.
Frost with whipped topping.
Sprinkle crushed candy over top.
Refrigerate, then enjoy.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and milk.
Place confectioners sugar in a small bowl.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough into the confectioners sugar.
Roll to coat and form into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on the cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes or until set. (If you want them chewy like Laura likes them, don't overbake.) Cool 1 minute, then remove from pans.

title: spanish rice
directions: Sift flour again with baking powder, cinnamon and salt into mixing bowl.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in milk, shortening and brown sugar.
Add to dry ingredients all at once and mix quickly. Stir in nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups and bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: pebbles cookie crisps
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water and egg in large bowl with a wooden spoon until well blended. Stir in cereal.

title: apple jacks
directions: Make into stiff dough.
Roll in small pieces.
Cook apples and sweeten.
Put small amount on dough and fold.
Fry in Crisco until brown.

title: banana cake with caramel frosting
directions: Cook cake mix according to package directions in 2 (8-inch) pans.
After cake is done, let cool and then slice each cake in two to form 4 layers.

title: orange slices candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.

title: corn pudding
directions: Prepare corn according to package directions. Drain well. In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, margarine and milk; mix well. Add corn to mixture and mix again. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Stir mixture well and pour into greased 8-inch square casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: canadian bacon-french toast sandwiches
directions: Brown slices of bacon in butter or margarine.
Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken and pepper in 2 quarts water and simmer, covered, for about 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth until almost tender. Drain and place in 2-quart shallow baking dish.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and rice together in a casserole dish.
In saucepan, melt margarine, Cheez Whiz and soup and add milk.
Mix together until melted.
Pour over broccoli and rice.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crisp delight
directions: Place apples in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Blend the margarine, sugar, flour and cinnamon; pack loosely over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: In large saucepan, add water to potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and carrots.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes; do not drain.
In separate pan, melt butter, then gradually stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly and maintaining medium heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir cheese sauce and ham into undrained vegetable mixture.
Heat for 20 minutes; do not boil.
This is good served with corn muffins.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick pie
directions: Pour fruit into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix dry over the top.
Spoon melted butter over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake and pecan frosting
directions: Sift all dry ingredients (except sugar) together; set aside. Mix oil, sugar and eggs, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: party chicken
directions: Cut up beef into strips and use them to line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Place chicken breasts on top of beef. In a separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream and cream cheese. Pour mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika as desired. Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours or at 325° for 1 hour. Chicken is done when meat thermometer reads 180° at thickest part of breast.

title: lemon pie
directions: Let Cool Whip thaw in refrigerator.
Mix lemonade, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Pour in pie crusts and refrigerate.
May add yellow food coloring for color.

title: salmon-cheese ball
directions: Drain salmon. Remove skin and bones.
Blend in cream cheese and lemon juice. Add onion, horseradish and salt.
Chill 4 hours. Shape into ball. Roll in almonds and chill again.
Serve with crackers.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf.
Recipe does not double well.

title: veggie dunk (dip)
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl or blender.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 1 cup of dip.
Good with all raw vegetables.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Cook until done but still firm. Drain; add the ingredients and chill.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water together until it forms a hard ball in water.
Add peanuts and boil until the syrup changes to a light caramel.
Add butter and soda.
Remove from heat and beat very hard for two or three minutes.
Turn out on buttered dish and as it cools, pull from the edges into sheets of almost paper thinness.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, ginger and allspice; set aside.
In another large bowl, combine oil, molasses, sugar and eggs.
With electric mixer on medium, beat 3 minutes until blended.
Add dry ingredients, beating until smooth and well blended.
Quickly stir in boiling water.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.

title: banana-oatmeal drops
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: braciole(bra-shoal)
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, cheese, garlic, egg and parsley to make a paste.
May need to add a little water to make stuffing workable.
Pat stuffing on meat and keep about 1/4 inch away from sides of meat.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Brown meat; drain fat.
Pour over spaghetti sauce and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Boil spaghetti about 1/2 hour before braciole is done. Serve spaghetti as side dish with braciole and top off with sauce. Serves 2 to 4.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: maple-y nut ice cream sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add nuts and cook over low heat until lightly browned.
Add Karo syrup and bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Serve warm on ice cream, pudding or plain cake. Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Combine all and heat in double boiler. Serves 6.

title: kraut salad
directions: Chop green pepper, celery, onion and pimentos.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and oil; add salt and pepper to your taste.
Heat to melt sugar, then cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Should stand for 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions; drain noodles.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir in the spinach and 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Spread Ricotta cheese mixture evenly on individual lasagna noodles.
Roll up each noodle.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in paper or plastic cups.
Cover with Saran Wrap and freeze.
To serve, partially thaw, eat and enjoy.
It's delicious.

title: sugar cookies (best)
directions: Cream together butter (oleo), sugar and eggs.
Add extract, flour, salt and soda and mix together.
Add this to creamed mixture and mix.
Divide dough into 3 parts and wrap in wax paper and put in refrigerator-freezer for 30 minutes, or refrigerate overnight.
Take out and put in lower refrigerator, taking out 1 part at a time.
Put on floured board and roll out to 3/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Slice and layer cream cheese in bottom of
8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Cover with a layer of the chili.
Add a layer of salsa.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Suggest 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar and vegetable oil. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together and add to oil mixture gradually. Fold carrots, nuts and pineapple into mixture. Bake in three 8-inch layers at 350° for approximately 40 minutes. Cool. Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Defrost and drain spinach well (can thaw in micro).
Drain artichoke hearts and cut in quarters.
Mix Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, chiles, spinach and artichoke heart pieces.
Pour mixture into quiche pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: olypian greek chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and vegetables.
Blend together salad dressing and garlic.
Pour over vegetables and chicken; toss to coat. Serve chilled on lettuce.
Store, refrigerated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marmalade - without pectin
directions: Remove peel from mandarins and lemons, lay peel flat, pare off and discard as much of the white part of peel as possible.
Cover with cold water and boil until peel is tender.
If the peel is quite bitter, change the water several times.
Chop fruit pulp, removing any seeds and membrane.
Combine pulp and peel and measure, pack the fruit down firmly.
To each cup of fruit add 2 cups of water and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Boil hard for 25 minutes, measure fruit and add an equal measure of sugar.
Boil to jelly stage.
Skim off foam and ladle into hot, sterilized glasses. Seal.
Makes seven 8 ounce glasses.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice set aside.
Melt margarine in frypan.
Thaw broccoli drain well.
Add broccoli and chopped onion to melted margarine and cook slow until onion is tender.
In a large bowl combine rice broccoli, add soups undiluted, you may need to add a little water so that mixture is not dry.
Grease a 13 x 9 inch casserole dish with margarine.
Pour mixture in and cover with wax paper and cook for 20 minutes 700 watt microwave or can be cooked in conventional oven for 30 minutes uncovered.
After cooking top with grated cheese.
Allow cheese to melt.
This casserole is good served with baked turkey, ham or baked chicken.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Finely crush soup mix; set aside.
Cream butter with grated cheese.
Add onion soup mix, flour and salt; mix well.
Shape into 4 rolls and freeze.
Remove from freezer and slice.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes after it boils; drain well.
Mix other ingredients with broccoli.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tina's caramel brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk in top of double boiler. Cook, stirring constantly until caramels are completely melted. Remove from heat.
Combine cake mix, remaining 1/3 cup milk and butter, mixing with mixer until dough holds together.
Dough will be very thick.
Stir in nuts.
Press half of cake mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; you may need to use a little more than half.
Then sprinkle chocolate bits over crust.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate bits, spreading evenly.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°. Cool and chill for 30 minutes before cutting.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix flour, pepper and mustard in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening, then fold in grated cheese.
Add enough milk to make a stiff dough that will still drop from a spoon.
Drop onto greased pan by tablespoons.
Brush tops with butter.
Sprinkle with garlic powder (parsley flakes optional).
Bake in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until nicely browned.

title: date nut squares
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Gradually add sugar and almond flavoring.
Crush soda crackers and add dates and nuts. Mix well and fold into egg white mixture.
Pour into square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook the shrimp and scallops briefly in water until just done (usually until water begins to reboil). Remove and refresh in cold water. Shell shrimp; dry scallops and shrimp.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and sugar.
Add nuts and press over pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes; let cool.

title: mabel d's pizza hot dish
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Drain.
Brown hamburger and chopped onions. Drain off grease.
Combine all ingredients except 8 ounces of grated Cheddar cheese.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 8 ounces of Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Bring broth, pepper and salt to rolling boil.
Stir flour and water which have been mixed well into broth.
Add 3 boiled eggs and giblets (liver, neck).

title: sugary crinkle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, cream together butter, shortening, sugars, vanilla and egg until fluffy.
In separate bowl, sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Mix to moderately stiff dough. Using about a tablespoon of dough for each cookie, roll dough into small balls.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Do not flatten!

title: clam dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Mix with mayo; add clams, then season with remaining ingredients (except bread) to taste.
Cut the middle out of large loaf of bread to form a bowl.
Fill with clam dip.
Cut excess bread and small loaf into bite-size cubes.
Chill.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg; mix well. Combine rhubarb and strawberries.
Line pie pan with pastry; fill with fruit.
Pour egg mixture over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Top with lattice crust; crimp edge high.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. If desired when serving, fill in a couple of openings in lattice top with whole, fresh strawberries.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
In separate pan, mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Pour into butter.
Stir to mix. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each one.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes until set. Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: easy no-bake cookieslubbock, texas
directions: Mix sugar and Karo and bring to a boil.
Boil 1/2 a minute. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.

title: easy mix candies
directions: Heat butter and milk over low heat.
Stir in frosting mix. Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until glossy and smooth. Add pecans or walnuts, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and eat.

title: pearfect green beans
directions: Place the pear slices in a saucepan with water and lemon peel; bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in the green beans and the salt; continue cooking.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Spoon batter into cupcake paper-lined muffin tin or into greased muffin tins 1/4 to 1/2 full. Sprinkle sugar on top of batter cups after you pour into muffin tin, then bake for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli crown
directions: Trim and discard outer leaves and tough stems from broccoli; chop and boil flowerets in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Stir in flour and Lawry's salt; cook and stir constantly just until bubbly.
Stir in milk; cook and stir sauce until it thickens and boils 1 minute.
Beat eggs slightly in a small bowl; stir in generous 1/2 cup of the hot sauce.
Quickly stir back into sauce in pan.
Cook, stirring, until mixture thickens.
Stir in mayonnaise and parsley.
Fold in drained broccoli.
Spoon into a well-greased 5-cup ring mold. Place ring in dish of water to bake.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Loosen sides and turn out onto a plate.
Serve.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Arrange broccoli in casserole dish.
Layer chicken over broccoli.
In small mixing bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well.
Spread over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
In a small bowl combine the bread crumbs with melted margarine, then sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle onions around and under chicken. Pour oil and wine over chicken.
Sprinkle with tarragon and black pepper.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes. Remove foil.
Turn oven up to 375°.
Place grapes around chicken. Bake uncovered for an additional 15 minutes.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Pour this mixture in an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil brown sugar, syrup and water until forms a soft ball. Beat 2 large egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup mixture over whites; beat until holds together good.
Dab out on waxed paper.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Bake in muffin pan at 350°.

title: egg breakfast casserole
directions: Melt oleo and pour half in bottom of pan.
Remove crusts from bread and arrange bread in pan.
Sprinkle meat and cheese over bread.
Beat eggs and milk and rest of oleo together and pour over entire slices of bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins ala cooper
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a very large bowl.
Add raisins (optional).
Make well in center and pour in eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir until mixed.
Cover; store up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in muffin pan.

title: strawberry preserve cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add oil and milk.
In another bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in preserves and nuts.
Pour into very well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir together margarine and sugar. Blend in cornmeal. Beat eggs with fork and add 1 at a time. Add juice but don't beat. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: mosette
directions: Drain boiled and blanched noodles; set aside.
Simmer together in a skillet the tomato soup, tomatoes, celery and soda.
In another skillet brown the onions, green peppers, pork and beef in bacon fat.
Stir in mushrooms and the cheese.
Add garlic and salt to taste.
Simmer until cheese is melted, then combine with noodles and tomato mixture.
Place all in 2 large glass casseroles and cook at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 20.

title: crullers
directions: Add flour to roll.
Fry in hot, deep oil or Crisco.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and mash to drain.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate peanut butter apples
directions: Wash
apples
and
dry thoroughly; insert wooden skewer into each
apple.
Set aside; melt chocolate chips and peanut butter chips
with oil in top of a double boiler or in a heavy 1
1/2 quart
saucepan
over low heat.
Stir constantly until smooth. Remove
from heat; dip apples in mixture (tilting pan as
needed) twirl
to remove excess coating.
Place apples on wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal mix and eggs.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased cast-iron pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes. Let set for about 10 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: sesame muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
In mixing bowl, mix eggs and all wet ingredients, add dry ingredients.
Mix only enough to blend ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until muffins are golden.
Serve with Mandarin Marmalade.
Makes 12.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: parmesan-herb bread
directions: Preheat broiler.
In small bowl, mix butter, grated Parmesan, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Slice bread horizontally in half.
Spread both cut sides with cheese mixture.
Place bread, cut sides up, on cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet on rack at closest position to source of heat; broil bread 1 to 2 minutes until cheese mixture is golden and bubbly.
Remove from broiler.
Sprinkle roasted red peppers over top of bread.
Cut each half into 4 pieces.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions until very well browned, but not scorched in butter; add chicken or beef broth and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
The soup is now put into a casserole. Cover with toasted French bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in a 275° oven for about 5 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: skewered turkey grill
directions: Cut turkey into 1-inch chunks. Thread on skewers, alternating with bell pepper squares and whole garlic cloves. On separate skewers, spear pineapple, zucchini and cherry tomatoes. Mix oil and seasonings; brush ingredients on skewers with oil. Cook skewers with turkey over hot coals 5 minutes. Place remaining skewers on grill; cook, basting occasionally, 10 minutes longer until turkey is done.

title: mustard marinated green beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients except beans and bring to a boil. Simmer and pour over beans. Refrigerate.

title: south of the border special
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in water, tomato sauce, chili powder and oregano.
Pour half the mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half the beans and half the chips.
Repeat layering.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining ingredients.
This serves 8 to 10 and is a good way to use up stale chip pieces at the bottom of the bag.

title: melon delight
directions: From each chilled melon, make 1 cup melon balls.
In parfait glasses, alternate layers of the 3 melon types.
Pour pineapple juice over melon.
Serve chilled.
Serves 4.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling and coffee.
Beat well with whisk until well blended, let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust - freeze until firm.
6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes.
Top with fudge sauce.

title: boneless chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle onion powder over roast.
Heat oil in deep pan with lid.
Brown roast in oil.
Add onion soup and place in preheated 325° oven with lid on.
After 40 minutes, add vegetables.
Replace lid and return to oven for 30 minutes.
Allow an extra 10 minutes for raw veggies.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook
chicken
in water with onion, celery with leaves, bay leaf,
3 to 4 peppercorns and salt.
Cook until tender (30 minutes).	Cook
broccoli	until
tender
and
drain.
Debone chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and seasonings. Arrange
drained
broccoli in casserole dish.
Sprinkle broccoli with Parmesan cheese.
Break chicken and spread over broccoli; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over all of it; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at
350° for
minutes.
Great served with yellow or brown rice.

title: red hot cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large stockpot.
Heat over medium heat until candies are melted.
Discard spices.
Serve hot.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: chocolate sodas
directions: For each soda place 2 to 3 tablespoons chocolate syrup in a tall glass.
Fill glass 1/2 full with beverage.
Add 2 scoops vanilla ice cream, stirring after each addition.
Fill glass with beverage.
Serve soda with large marshmallow and red maraschino cherry on a straw.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Add egg yolks, sugar, butter, soda and buttermilk; set aside. Pour bourbon over raisins and let stand about 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Add pecans, dates, cherries, pineapple, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and flour.
Mix with the egg yolk mixture and the bourbon and raisins.
Fold in the whites last.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes in round casserole. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: john's mother's dressing
directions: Toast bread and cut into 1-inch cubes or tear into small pieces.
Add corn bread, crumbled (put in large bowl).
Saute chopped onion in butter until yellow.
Add to bread and corn bread mixture.
Add poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Let stand 1 hour or overnight, if possible.
Add well beaten egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in broth from turkey and mix well.
Put in greased baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut into strips.
In skillet, cook 1/2 of chicken in margarine over medium-high heat 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Cook remaining chicken and onion 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Return all chicken to skillet.
Add salsa and taco seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Heat beans.
On baking sheet, arrange shells, overlapping as necessary.
Heat in oven 5 to 7 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat 1/2 cup sugar into egg yolks; add salt.
Stir in milk. Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Add vanilla and 7-Up; stir.
Chill.
Dot with whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: meal in a bowl chicken soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil in a 4-quart saucepan over high heat. Add carrots and celery.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add peas, corn and chicken. Cover and simmer about 4 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in macaroni, pepper and parsley.
Heat through. Makes 2 quarts.

title: crab boats
directions: Bake potatoes.
Slit and take potato from skins.
Beat potato with warm milk and butter.
Mix crab with potato and pile back into skins.
Put cheese on top and put under broiler to melt.

title: spice tea
directions: Add 1 to 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and bananas.
Blend together flour, soda and salt.
Add this slowly to banana mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased (8x4x3) loaf pans at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Do not over bake.

title: homemade kraut
directions: Wash and shred cabbage.
In a large 3-gallon churn, start with a layer of cabbage, then canning salt.
Pack hard after each layer.
Keeping layering and packing until churn is almost full, pack until water rises to top.
Put a large rock in a plastic bag; put in churn to hold mixture down.
Tie a cloth on top tightly. Let set 7 days.
Take from churn, boil kraut and put in pint jars. Seal.

title: punch
directions: Thaw frozen juices.
Combine all ingredients with ginger ale in a punch bowl.

title: quick crab soup
directions: Mix all together and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems from mushrooms; finely chop mushroom stems.
In a non-metal bowl, micro-cook cream cheese, uncovered, on 30% power (Medium-low) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until soft.
Then stir together cream cheese and other ingredients, including chopped mushroom stems.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and Karo.
Add crunchy peanut butter. Pour over flakes.
Mix and drop on waxed paper to cool.
Or place in casserole dish and cool.
Then cut into squares.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put dry yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Let rise about 15 minutes.
Beat egg, sugar and shortening with about 3/4 cup milk. Mix well.
Add flour; mix again.
Add remaining milk; mix well. Knead on floured paper.
Put in bowl.
Let stand 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Roll out in small biscuits.
Should make 20 rolls.

title: banana crush
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Use pineapple juice to blend bananas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in 6 cup portions. Take out of freezer 4 hours before using.
Use 1 six cup portion with 2 bottles lemon lime soda.
Entire recipe serves 60.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together apples, lemon juice, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup brown sugar and pour into margarine.
Mix together flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar, salt and milk.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle some cinnamon sugar on top before baking.	Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Serve with ice cream

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart dish. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Blend well. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and gently stir until foamy.
Pour onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool. Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: "garbage"
directions: Melt in microwave the chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over Rice Chex, raisins and peanuts.
Stir until coated.
Pour into large garbage bag. Add confectioners sugar. Shake up.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Heat together the soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, grated onion and 1/2 cup cheese.
Add grated potatoes.
Let mixture set overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: corny casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake 1 hour.

title: make ahead mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mash and add oleo or butter, onion salt and sour cream.
Put in baking dish; refrigerate overnight.
Put in 350° oven.
Sprinkle on grated cheese and bake for 1 hour.

title: disappearing cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in eggs. Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a bowl, adding alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake tests done and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Use cocoa in your favorite frosting.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add seasonings and sauce. Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream and onions.
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, beef and sour cream mixture in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
To prevent sticking, layer sauce on bottom of pan.

title: star bright cookies
directions: Mix together in order given.
Form into balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
After about 6 minutes of baking, press chocolate star on top of each cookie.

title: barbecue chestnuts
directions: Wrap 1/2 strip of bacon around a whole water chestnut.
Secure with a toothpick.
Broil until bacon is done.
Pour barbecue sauce over them and heat.

title: dolly's oatmeal bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, oil, molasses, salt and boiling water to together and set aside.
When mixture is cool add yeast and flour.
Knead and let rise.
Poke down and put in tins to rise again.

title: firehouse multi-bean salad
directions: Combine veggies in one bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and 3/4 cup water; salt and pepper.
Pour over beans and veggies. Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Toss.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, soup, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
(Save a little of the butter.)
Crumble cornflakes on top. Drizzle butter over the cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix. Sprinkle with a layer of coconut.
Drizzle with melted butter. Top with pecan halves or chopped nuts.
Bake att 350° until brown.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add vanilla, egg, carrots and the remaining ingredients, adding the raisins last. Drop on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream Crisco; add sugar and continue to cream.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder and beat alternately with buttermilk. Add melted chocolate, then vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In a large pot, put stewed tomatoes, tomato soup, 2 cloves garlic, 1/2 cup water, beef bouillon and sugar; bring to a boil.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Blend all ingredients (except roast) on high speed.
Marinate roast for 3 days.

Remove roast from the marinade and brown. After you have browned the meat, pour marinade over roast in Dutch oven or covered roaster and simmer on top of stove for 4 hours or bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl (if mixing by hand) or into your large mixing machine bowl (using dough hooks) and stir until Crisco is melted, salt and sugar dissolved.
Cool mixture.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Beat and add egg to mixture.
Add 2 cups of flour and mix thoroughly, slowly stirring or mixing remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Place dough in a warm bowl that has been greased with vegetable oil; again, grease top of dough to prevent drying out while raising and cover lightly with wax paper and towel.
You may at this point, place mixture in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or raise immediately on your counter top.

After raising, press dough mixture down and shape into large or small rolls that are placed on a greased baking sheet (lightly greasing top of each roll with vegetable oil) to raise for 1 to 2 hours until rolls touch on all sides.
Bake on middle shelf of oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When rolls are finished baking, melt a half a stick of butter/margarine and base each roll.
Doubling this recipe will give you about 2 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Mix 1/2 cake mix (dry), margarine, brown sugar, water and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and 1 cup nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until marshmallows are puffed and golden brown. Heat frosting, stirring constantly, until thin.
Drizzle over top. Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: reuben pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Press bread slices in bottom to cover entire bottom.
Spread mustard over bread.
Place cheese, beef and Kraut on top.
In medium bowl combine eggs and milk.
Beat together. Pour egg mixture over pie.
Bake at 325 for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate for at least a half hour.
Mix well before serving.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together and let stand for 1 hour.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to apple mixture.
Beat eggs with vanilla and add oil and nuts.
Add mixtures together and pour in a greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: weight watchers pie
directions: Roll bread thin. Grate apple.
Add sweetener. Spread on bread. Put on pan in oven at 350° for 20 minutes. When done, spread oleo on. Add cinnamon.
If desired, add cheese.
Can use banana or fresh peaches in place of apple.

title: creamy white icing
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed for 3 minutes, then mix at high speed for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in layers in 9 x 13-inch cake pan:
cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over fruit; sprinkle with nuts.
Pour oleo evenly over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Chop artichoke hearts.
Add 1 cup bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, olive oil and a dash of garlic powder.
Add water from artichoke hearts.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and save the broth.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set; cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: delightful peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients except bell peppers.
Cut peppers lengthwise and hollow out.
Fill stuffing mix and place in baking pan or microwave-safe dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: peanut butter chippies
directions: Combine brown sugar, peanut butter, oleo, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in the chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 7 to 8 minutes, or until set and just beginning to brown. Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to rack to cool completely.

title: bachelor's casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef.
Brown well and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Place pineapple and sugar in a saucepan and boil about 5 minutes.
Add jello to pineapple; stir until dissolved.
Cool lightly.
Beat cream cheese and evaporated milk until very foamy, about 5 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Add jello and pineapple mixture to milk and cheese; keep folding until color is even and foam disappears.
Chill in a large mold or in mixing bowl. Delicious!

title: tomato meat spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large saucepot, coat the bottom with olive oil.
Brown chopped garlic.
Crumble the ground beef into the pot and brown. You may use your own variety of meats (meatballs, Italian hot sausage removed from casing, pork chops, sirloin steak or ground beef).
Once the meat is browned, add the tomato paste, the water, the tomatoes, the oregano, the salt and pepper, the mint and the hot sauce.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour over medium heat; stir now and again.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 hours over medium-low heat, stirring now and again.
If heat is too high sauce will stick to bottom of pan.

title: best icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat with mixer 3 to 5 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.
Keep covered when you aren't using.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan.
Cook very slowly until mixture thickens.
Serve over ice cream or desserts.

title: evelyn's old-fashioned coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add egg yolks. Beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add alternately with the milk to the butter mixture. Add vanilla. Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter. Pour into three 9-inch well-greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool well before icing.

title: toasty onion sticks
directions: Blend together margarine and soup mix.
Spread this on trimmed bread.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sugar cutouts
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Work flour into creamed mixture.
Wrap dough in foil or plastic wrap and chill until firm.
Roll dough on a floured board a bit at a time, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes, or until firm and golden on edges.

title: broccoli bites
directions: Pull broccoli into bite size pieces; peel stem and slice. Combine all ingredients in large bowl, using enough mayonnaise (not salad dressing) to hold mixture together.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: baked buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add chicken and turn each piece several times to coat.
Bake turning chicken twice until cooked through, about 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in 8-inch square cake pan (greased) in 325° oven for 35 minutes.

title: modified low-fat brownie banana split pie
directions: Make brownies in large 11 x 14-inch pan (spray with Pam or Mazola); let cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix well with sugar.

title: italian spinach soup with meatballs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in soup kettle.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Combine ground beef, bread, egg, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls and cook in large nonstick skillet until browned. Add meat balls to broth and vegetables; cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and nuts.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; spread on buns.
Add ham and one slice cheese.
Wrap each in foil.
Put in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix with the melted margarine and almost half of the can of milk. Spread half of the batter in greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: raspberry snow(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Boil the milk and water; sprinkle in the washed sago and cook thoroughly.
Add the sugar.
