Allow to cool and beat up with the raspberry jam and the lemon juice.
Add a little red colouring matter if liked.
Serve alone or with fruit.
(WCB)

title: crock-pot cube steak
directions: Slice cube steak in pieces.
Cook all ingredients in crock-pot all day.
May want to add more cream of mushroom soup.

title: cabbage-bean soup
directions: In large saucepan sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray, saute onion until tender.
Add water, ham, cabbage, tomatoes and pepper.
Bring to boil; lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Continue simmering for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream and cucumber salad(serves 12, kinda)
directions: Mix
salt, sugar and vinegar thoroughly.
Then add sour cream and stir until smooth.
Adjust mixture to taste (not too sweet). Then
add
chives,
dill and celery seed.
Next slice cuke very thin,
leave
peel
on.
Finally
mix thinly sliced cucumber and dressing and chill for at least 4 hours.

title: date pinwheel refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, then add all dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half and roll out.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl measure first 9 ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat until mixed.
Increase speed to high and beat 5 minutes, scraping bowl with spatula.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on wire rack.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Blend
butter, sugar, vanilla, salt and juice;
beat in eggs one at a time.
Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add to egg mixture. Fold
in
flour,
nuts, preserves and food coloring. Pour
batter into 2 large greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bread pulls away from pan.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Roll into balls in powdered sugar and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add onion, 15 crackers, milk, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and put into casserole dish.
Crush remaining crackers; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Heat the ham in a skillet with the butter.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour the mixture over the ham and mix. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: captain's chowder
directions: Brown bacon
and onion until bacon is almost crisp. Add rest of ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Mix ginger, garlic, water, lemon juice, seasoned salt, garlic powder and onion powder (amounts may be increased) for marinade.

title: herbed cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, buttermilk and melted butter. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.
Good served with basil butter.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and
stem	mushrooms
and dice stems.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Saute
onion,
pepper and stems until onion is translucent.
Add	Worcestershire	sauce,	garlic	salt, oregano and parsley flakes, mixing well.
Add diced bread; mix well. Remove from heat.
Add cheese; mix until melted.
Stuff caps. Brown in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crazy pie
directions: Melt butter in baking pan (8 or 9 inch pan) while oven heats at 350 degrees;
set butter aside.
Combine flour, sugar and half of milk;
stir until ingredients are moistened.
Add rest of milk; stir until smooth.
Pour over melted butter, do not stir.
Place fruit over batter;
do not stir.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes until crust is brown.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine zucchini and oil. Blend eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts. Blend well.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Ice after cool.

title: herbed waldorf salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Toss gently.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and gently toss with apple mixture.
Chop ferns from fennel and fold into salad.
Cover. Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for Certo.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add Certo and pour into jars.

title: cocoa-fudge icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until nice and creamy, adding the sugar a small amount at a time.
If too thin, add a little more sugar.
Top with walnuts or pecans.

title: instant hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
When needed, fill cup half full of mix and add hot water.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom and sides of an 11 x 7 inch baking dish.
Chop the onion.
Heat butter in a small non-stick skillet over medium-high heat until melted.
Stir in onion.
Saute until tender.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except coconut. Cook on medium heat until thick. Remove from heat; add coconut and mix well. Use as filling between layers and on top.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Put navy beans, salt and pepper, onion, celery and ham in slow cooker.
Cover with water, just a little above all the ingredients. Can start the night before and let it cook all night on high.
In morning, turn cooker to low and add potatoes and until you need or want it for supper, it will be done.
(You can double or triple this recipe if you want to make a big pot of soup.)
This will have to be made in a large crock-pot.
Don't forget to stir occasionally.

title: pecan pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Batter will be lumpy even without the nuts.
Bake on hot griddle.
To keep pancakes warm until all are baked, put them in the oven at the lowest temperature.
To serve, arrange on a platter in an overlapping pattern and garnish with twisted orange slices.
Makes about sixteen 4-inch pancakes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, Crisco or oleo.
Add confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour.
Mix well and add chopped pecans.

title: bean dip ole
directions: Combine beans, chilies and milk.
Add Velveeta.
Stir over low heat until cheese spread melts.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: french stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms dry with damp cloth.
Remove stems and mince. Saute stems and scallions in butter 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Add cream, sherry, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickens, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Set aside ready to broil.
Place under broiler just enough to slightly brown.

title: roast water fowl
directions: Rub cavities of birds with onion and garlic.
Combine butter, paprika, salt and Tabasco sauce; rub into duck skin.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Cook in salt water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add egg, flour, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Spray skillet well.
Cook at medium-high heat, turn once.
When browned on both sides, remove from heat.

title: swiss steak with gravy
directions: Rub steak with flour to coat generously.
Brown in oil in a large heavy skillet.
Remove steak; set aside.
Saute onion and celery until tender in same skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients and return steak to skillet and cover.
Simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat from gravy.
Let gravy stand in pan about a minute or until grease rises to top.
Skim off grease. Heat gravy again to boiling.
Slice steak.
Serve with hot gravy and creamed potatoes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to directions on package.
When cool, crumble into small pieces.
Chop tomatoes, onion and pepper and mix with cornbread.
Sprinkle with Salad Supreme.
Add mayonnaise and bacon bits and mix.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: fish in dill sauce
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a shallow casserole with fish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: freezer bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, spices and salt and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Put veggies into containers (I use Cool Whip containers) and fill about 3/4 full.
Pour liquid over and cover. These may be frozen or refrigerated, depending on how fast you use them.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Break up burger into water.
Cook until done (5 to 10 minutes).
Add seasonings and soup mix.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes (blended), vegetables and orzo.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook Orzo.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Cut very fine the celery.
Add to bowl.
Also cut fine green or red pepper; add. Mince scallions; add.
Grate some red onion (to taste).
Mix everything together.
Add sea legs.
Sprinkle lemon juice to taste.
Mix in mayonnaise to taste.
Chill before serving.
Makes enough to serve 4 to 6 people.

title: spicy marmalade bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread bread with butter, then marmalade. Sprinkle cinnamon generously on marmalade.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes or until hot.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Bring juice to boil and add to jello, then beat in cream cheese; cool.
Add fruit. Refrigerate.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop vegetables and cook down.
Add remaining ingredients in saucepan and cook slowly for 1 to 2 hours or until sauce is of desired consistency.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
In separate bowl, mix buttermilk and baking soda.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Combine in water the cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cook until thick.
Beat the egg whites well, then add 5 tablespoons sugar.
Add to cooked mixture.
Beat good with hand beater.
Put on pie and brown.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Gather enough blackberries to overflow a pie pan.
After rinsing, pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle sugar over blackberries. Cover with second pie shell.
Spread margarine over top of pie crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven until crust browns (about 40 minutes).

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in buttermilk for 15 minutes.
Stir in sugar. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate-peanut cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar, beating at low speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: roasted garlic and almond dip
directions: Set oven to 300°.
Use lowest rack.
Place garlic in small dish and toss with vegetable oil.
Bake until soft, 30 minutes. Transfer to blender and let cool, 30 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mustard to garlic; blend.
Scrape into bowl, stir in almonds, sour cream, mayo and herbs.
Salt and pepper, if desired. Cover and refrigerate.

title: crusty white bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups of the flour and yeast. Add water, cooking oil, sugar and salt to dry mixture.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla; add eggs.
Beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture.
Blend well.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until they begin to pull away from the edges of the pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
I double to make a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice boiled potatoes in bowl.
Add onion, cut small.
Cut bacon in pan and render until bacon is brown.
Remove bacon and put in sliced potatoes.
Measure bacon grease.
Add flour and stir over heat until it bubbles.
Add water and vinegar mixed together. Stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar. Let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Pour over potatoes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wet burritos
directions: Mix and cook for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Put meat mixture in flour tortilla shells.
Roll up and place seam down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butternut squash and apple bake
directions: Peel and slice squash and apples.
Layer into a slightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle walnuts over layers.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn flake chicken
directions: Line pan with aluminum foil.
Skin chicken.
Take chicken and sprinkle with Lawry's.
Dip in butter and roll in cornflakes. Place in pan covering with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: night hawk corn bread muffin
directions: Mix well.
Pour into hot greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple-less pie
directions: Boil sugar, cream of tartar and water for 1 minute.
Add Ritz crackers and boil for 2 minutes.
Take off stove and add lemon juice.
Pour in pie crust; sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Cover with second crust.
Don't perforate or split top crust.
Bake in a 400° oven until crust is nicely brown, about 25 minutes.
Good warm.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Combine cottage cheese, spinach, 8 ounces Mozzarella cheese in a large bowl.
Cook pasta shells until tender.
Stuff pasta shells with cottage cheese mixture.
Pour 8 ounces of pasta sauce in baking pan.
Place stuffed shells in baking pan.
Pour remainder of pasta sauce on top of shells.
Sprinkle remainder of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amish church soup
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add beans and milk.
Bring to the boiling point.
Add bread crumbs.
Serves 15.

title: raisin bars
directions: Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.
Mix the oats, flour, sugar, butter, soda and salt.
Add 1/2 cup of hot water and mix well.
Split dough in half.
Roll half out onto cookie sheet.
Add raisin mixture on top.
Roll out remaining crust and put on top of raisin mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: delicious dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a bowl, cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix in flour until easy to handle.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Punch down with greased hand.
Pinch off small pieces and roll into balls.
Place on greased pan to rise 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen medium size rolls.

title: chocolate pudding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pudding mix and baking mix together.
Add oil and egg.
Form mixture into 1/2-inch balls. Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press thumb into middle of each ball to make a thumbprint.
Place chips or other candies in thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Separate crackers and place on foil (tight fit). Boil margarine, butter, sugar and vanilla together on low heat until bubbly. Slowly pour boiled mixture
over crackers.
Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cheese cake supreme
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, juice,
vanilla
and salt, mixing until
well blended.
Add eggs, one at
a
time.
Beat well after each addition. Place crust on
baking
sheet.
Pour in the filling.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pie filling
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add pumpkin.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add canned milk and mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine beef, bread, eggs, onion, salt and oregano.
Stir in 3/4 cup tomato sauce.
Press meat on wax paper.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with mushrooms.
Roll and place in pan with seam down.
Bake for 30 minutes; drain drippings.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf. Bake 30 more minutes.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 375°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dry hot dog; heat oil. Mix flour and corn meal. Cut in shortening. Add milk and egg. Stir to mix. Dip hot dogs in batter; let excess batter drip off. Fry in hot oil, turning, until all sides are browned. Drain on paper towels. Place wooden skewers in end of each.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Put sugar and Crisco in a bowl and blend.
In a large bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Set aside. Combine tomato soup, water and baking soda.
Add to Crisco mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili con carne
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a Dutch oven or large saucepan. Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add next 12 ingredients; stir to blend.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 (about 1 1/3 cups) servings.

title: grandma's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until light golden brown. Makes 2 pies.

title: mexican broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add Velveeta and soup.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is completely melted.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in pie shells.
Bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, until filling is golden brown and firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers and put half into bottom of large casserole dish. Add half of melted oleo. Add chicken and chestnuts. Mix soups, sour cream and water together and pour over chicken mixture. Add other half of crackers and oleo on top. Bake in 400° oven about 40 minutes. Makes large dish (3-quart). Very tasty.

title: ugly salad
directions: Cook 1 pound curly macaroni.
Add to mixture of ingredients. Let stand overnight.
Add 1 sliced onion and 2 sliced cucumbers to garnish, then enjoy!

title: fancy fast chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Lay mushrooms over cheese. Mix can of soup with wine and pour over chicken.
Spread stuffing over top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: st. louie potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Defrost hash browns.
In a large bowl mix onion, sour cream, margarine, soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Stir in potatoes, chives and parsley. Spread in prepared pan.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with bacon slice and secure with toothpick.
Grease baking dish and cover bottom with dried beef. Arrange bacon wrapped breasts on beef; combine soup and sour cream and pour over breasts.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: beat and eat icing
directions: Blend all ingredients, except water.
Add water and beat for 7 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: moe's chili
directions: Brown all the meat in the pot.
Drain partially.
Add onions, peppers, parsley, garlic and chili mix (per the instructions) and cook until the onions are clear.
Add tomatoes, sauce, cinnamon, brown sugar and the rest of the chili mix.
Cook, covered, on medium-low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese sprinkled on top.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, graham crackers and powdered sugar. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cut into squares after cooled completely.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken and Veg-All in casserole. Mix broth and soup together.
Pour on top of chicken and Veg-All.
Slice butter on top of this.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix shortening, cocoa, eggs, sugar and flour.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir together sweetened condensed milk, coconut and almonds.
Spread over partially baked hot crust.
Return to oven for 15 minutes more.
Let cool.
Combine chocolate, confectioners sugar, cream, butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cooled bars.

title: scotchies
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over low heat.
Blend in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla and flour.
Mix thoroughly; stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: shrimp tomato aspic salad
directions: Bring to boil tomato sauce, water, lemon juice, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Add jello and stir to dissolve. When firm, add celery, onions, and shrimp. Set unitl firm in 8 in. square pan or 1 qt. container.

title: al's country style vegetables
directions: Place the water in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add the onion, garlic, bouillon cubes and celery.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add the tomato sauce, chopped tomatoes, okra, greens and corn. Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in pieces before cooking, in about thirds. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Toss with salad dressing.

title: glazed bananas
directions: Combine orange juice, brown sugar, butter and orange peel in large skillet.
Heat until butter is melted.
Add bananas; heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Serve over ice cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese, broccoli soup
directions: In Dutch oven or stockpot, melt margarine.
Add onion and saute until transparent.
Add water and bouillon cubes; bring to a boil. Break Top Ramen into pieces.
Add with seasoning to boiling water. Return to boil and cook 3 minutes.
Add broccoli; return to boil. Cook 5 minutes.
Turn heat to low.
Add milk and Velveeta, cut in chunks.
Stir occasionally.
Ready to eat when cheese is melted.

title: brauer's sausage cakes(a southern recipe)
directions: Take approximately 1/2 loaf of white bread and break into pieces.
Take 3/4 of the package of sausage and tear into small pieces.
Take the eggs, crack and put in mixing bowl.
Add the bread and hunks of sausage and mix.
Add some milk every so often. Form into 4 to 5 cakes (looks like large hamburgers) and fry in large skillet with butter until golden brown.
Serve with fresh applesauce and cinnamon rolls.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Drain peas and place in a bowl.
Whisk oils, lemon juice, vinegar and garlic together and pour over peas.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving. Serves 16.

title: red cabbage salad(rodkalsalat)
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly. Chill.

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and green bell pepper in butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup of this mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Form into a loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve remaining sauce cold or heated over meat loaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix until smooth and pour into browned pie crust.

title: low-fat yogurt
directions: Mix milk and dry milk solids in a medium saucepan.
Heat to scalding (150°); cool to 110°.
Stir in yogurt.
Transfer mixture to a glass or crockery bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap; wrap bowl securely in a heavy bath towel.
Set in warm place (100° to 125°) for 4 to 6 hours until yogurt has formed.
Place several layers of paper toweling directly on yogurt; refrigerate covered until cold. Makes about 1 quart.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed. Pour batter in pan. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Check with tooth pick until clean. In a 11 x 14 pad add stick butter in pan. Put in oven, preheated at 350°. until butter melted. Sprinkle brown sugar, sprinkle pecans. Lay sliced pineapple and spread with crushed pineapple.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: joy's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour (salt added) to butter mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use icing of your choice.

title: hot buttered rum batter
directions: Blend all ingredients; store in freezer.
To serve, mix 1 tablespoon of batter and 1 jigger rum in a mug; fill with hot water.

title: lemon pie(makes 2)
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix milk and egg yolks.
Stir in lemon juice. Cook and stir until thick.
Divide between 2 pie shells.
Beat egg whites with 3/4 cup sugar until meringue stands in stiff peaks. Cover pies.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: To the beaten eggs, add the other ingredients (not the pecans).
Place the pecans (whole or pieces; makes no difference) in the bottom of the unbaked pie shell.
Pour on the other ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 325° or longer, depending on your oven.
The top should be nicely browned (don't overcook).

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Make white sauce in double boiler using butter, flour and milk; add salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Stir constantly to prevent lumping.
Five minutes before serving, add cooked chopped broccoli.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Fry everything together in a pan on top of stove.
Let simmer until your peppers and tomatoes are done.
Then add your macaroni and serve.

title: velveeta and tomato fondue
directions: Heat a fondue pot. Rub the garlic against the inside of the pot. Add the chopped tomato. Cook the tomato over very low heat for several minutes. Add the tomato juice and bring it to a boil. Sprinkle the flour over the cheeses. With a wooden spoon, add the cheeses to the pot, stirring slowly until the mixture is smooth. Place the pot over a fondue warmer and invite guests to stick skewered pieces of bread and vegetables into it.

title: krinkle face molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Mix and sift flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Mix all well. Roll into small balls.
Dip in sugar and bake about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: squash-rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Stir well after first half hour baking.

title: reuben sausage casserole
directions: Partially boil potatoes in water and drain.
Brown ground sausage in skillet.
Put all ingredients together (except the cheese) and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The last 5 or 10 minutes, add the shredded Swiss cheese on top to melt.

title: homemade mayonnaise dressing
directions: Beat the yolk in a mixing bowl, adding some olive oil drop by drop. When mixture begins to thicken, alternately add a few drops of lemon juice and a few drops more of olive oil until the desired consistency is obtained. Lemon juice thins the dressing and olive oil thickens it. If more lemon juice is added, oil must also be added, as the dressing must be stiff when ready to use. Refrigerate. Use within 2 to 3 days.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Batter chicken.
Fry until brown; drain grease.
Add box of Rice-A-Roni.
Cover with water.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice is done.

title: coffee cake
directions: Blend
first
ingredients with a pastry cutter.
Set aside one
cup of the mixture.
Put the remaining mixture into a mixing bowl
and
blend in the 1 cup buttermilk, 2 eggs and the 1 teaspoon soda.
Put into 2 round cake pans and sprinkle the 1 cup of reserved crumbs on top.	Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole #2
directions: Note:
Do not use metal spoon or bowl for mixing and do not refrigerate.
If air gets in the bag, let it out.
It is normal for the batter to bubble, thicken and ferment.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let stand several hours, preferably overnight.
Relish keeps well.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: In 2 tablespoons of butter, brown onion, bell pepper and mushrooms; take up and put in a casserole dish.
Brown chicken in same butter.
When done, layer on top of onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Mix soup, gravy and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over fettucini noodles.
Serves about 6.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix
ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: light date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let stand 10 minutes.

title: christmas morning strata
directions: Night before serving, grease 13 x 9 glass baking dish.
Cook sausage meat, using slotted spoon remove sausage to paper towel to drain.
Cut bread into 1/2 inch cubes.
Drain and chop mushrooms. In baking dish combine meat, bread and mushrooms.
In large bowl, whisk together eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour egg mixture over sausage mixture.
Cover baking dish with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy curry(lamb or turkey)
directions: Saute onion in shortening until tender.
Add curry powder and ginger.
After a couple of minutes, add soup (thinned per directions on can).
Next, add meat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Combine
butter,
hot
water, salt and sugar until dissolved. Add
yeast,
pumpkin, raisins and cinnamon.
Add half of
flour and stir.
Add remainder of flour until a soft, firm dough
is formed.
Knead for 5 minutes; dough will be sticky. Let rise until double, then shape and rise until double.
Bake at
for
20 minutes.
Makes
2 dozen.
Can be iced when cool.
A lot like a hot cross bun but better.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, butter and milk.
Boil 5 minutes (soft ball stage on candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring, peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until Marshmallow Creme is melted.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: apple-pumpkin butter
directions: Put all ingredients in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally until as thick as pudding.
Scrape into jars; cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a bowl mix crushed graham crackers with 1 stick of melted butter or margarine.
Put graham crackers in 9 x 12-inch cake pan for the crust.
Chill for a while.
Take another bowl and mix crushed pineapple, cream cheese and 1/2 stick butter together. Spread evenly on graham cracker crust.

title: easy jalapeno dip
directions: In a container of an electric blender or food processor, combine cream cheese and tomatoes.
Blend until smooth.
Add chilies; blend well.
Serve with fresh veggies or nacho chips.

title: malasadas
directions: Heat ingredients in a pot to lukewarm.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups. Bring to a boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl; add boiling liquid and stir to dissolve.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese; blend well.
Pour into bowl and chill 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn down to 375° and bake for 25 minutes more, until pie is set.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onion and soup mixture, starting with potatoes.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. If potatoes are raw, cooking time will be longer.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with lots of tortilla chips.
All it involves is can opening!!

title: coconut muffins
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and egg; beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; stir just until blended.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink ambrosia salad
directions: Mix everything together. Refrigerate.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In 8 x 12-inch dish, smooth cherry pie filling on bottom of dish, then crushed pineapple.
On that sprinkle sugar.
Smooth dry cake mix on that.
Pour melted margarine over, then chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked chicken batter
directions: Mix all ingredients and batter chicken.
Place in a greased pan and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: red hot applesauce
directions: Melt red hots in very small amount of water.
Add to applesauce.
Chill and serve.

title: curry tomato bisque
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add curry powder, salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add chicken broth, carrots, rice and tomatoes.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Flavor to taste with salt and pepper, if necessary.
Add cream and milk just before serving.
Do not boil.
Add a little butter at the end (optional).

title: chocolate coffee royale
directions: Place ice cream in large (8 to 12 ounce) tempered glass goblet or mug.
Pour liqueurs over ice cream.
Carefully and slowly, pour hot coffee over top of ice cream.
Top with whipped cream. Sprinkle with shaved chocolate and top with cherry.
Makes one serving.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine water, pineapple and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add lemon jello (2 small or 1 large).
Put in refrigerator until partly jelled.
Add Dream Whip and cheese.
Pour in mold.
Refrigerate.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Layer all in a greased casserole (meat, onions, carrots, soup and wine mixed).
Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: tropical dump cake
directions: Drain 1 can crushed pineapple and spread both cans of pineapple on bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Dot evenly with butter; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and bubbly. Serve with ice cream or topping.

title: shandy(a british drink.  serve on a hot "out of africa" afternoon.)
directions: In a chilled mug, combine the beer and lemonade.
Add ice, if desired.

title: jello tea cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Mix flour with baking powder.
Cream butter and gelatin, beating well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Roll out cookie dough and cut out shapes or force dough through a cookie press onto a ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: red devil
directions: Mix together deviled ham and cream cheese; form into a ball and roll in ground pecan crumbs.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: This was served at my mother's 80th birthday party.

title: sesame oat crackers
directions: Blend
cashews,
water
and dates smooth (soak dates in hot water
to
soften).
Add
mixture to other ingredients in bowl. Mix
well.
Pat
thin into sprayed pan and bake at 325° until golden brown.
Cool and cut.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water and drain. Mix other ingredients together and pour over cooled potatoes and fold together.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter, vanilla, graham cracker crumbs and butter with hands.
Roll into balls.
Melt together chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in this mixture and place on wax paper.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half crosswise.
Scoop out seeds and place in a baking dish.
Mix honey, butter, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Place half of this mixture in each section of squash.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and
milk until a drop of ingredients dropped in water forms
a
soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Beat
until thick.
Pour on pan.
Let cool, then cut.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Thaw veggies.
Saute veggies with onion in 3 tablespoons butter, about 3 minutes.
Add soup and sour cream; mix well.
Add 1 cup croutons and mix.

title: grandmaw's breakfast cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Add a little milk to make the mixture stiff.
Bake on greased pan at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: american cheese fondue
directions: Heat milk and margarine until margarine is melted.
In blender, put flour, onion soup mixture and cheese, cut in cubes.
Add hot milk mixture.
Cover and blend on high until smooth.
Pour into fondue pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until thickens.
Reduce heat to maintain slight bubbling during serving.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar, a little at a time, and beat until smooth. Begin adding eggs, one at a time.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into well greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Put tortilla chips in bottom of pan.
Pour meat over shells, then add more chips.
Grate the cheese; add on top of shells.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Can also add the brown beans to the meat mixture.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break up bread into an oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add sausage and cheese that has been cut into bite size pieces.
Add milk to eggs and beat well. Add salt, pepper and mustard; pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Remove from grease.
Saute onions and celery in meat grease.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
When ready to serve, float orange sherbet on top.
Makes about 30 cups.

title: rice-kraut dish
directions: Season and flour meat, brown in oil (covered dish), add rice, water
and top with sauerkraut.
Cover and bake in 350° oven until rice is tender.
Add more water if needed.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; continue cooking until onion and pepper are soft.
Add salt and pepper, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, Tabasco sauce and ripe olives.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chinese beef
directions: Mix together and heat well.
Serve over mixed rice.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: peg martin's ginger cookies
directions: Beat sugar, molasses, shortening
and
egg until smooth. Mix dry ingredients together and
add gradually until batter is smooth.
Chill 4 hours or
overnight
(covered).
Roll
out
on floured board and cut into	desired
shapes.
Place
on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes
Cool
thoroughly and ice with a dab of lemon icing.

title: own crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Bake in oiled pie plate for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: foam goody candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar. Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Cook without stirring until it reaches 285° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add soda immediately.
Stir through and immediately pour onto buttered jelly roll pan.
Do not spread out even if it doesn't cover pan. Cool.
Break in bite-size chunks. Melt the sweet chocolate over hot water.
Dip chunks of candy in chocolate. Place on waxed paper to cool. Store in airtight containers.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: summer fruit salad for a crowd
directions: Pour enough orange juice over top to almost cover.
A cup or two of pineapple juice adds just enough sweetener.
Serve well chilled either by itself or over sherbet.
Recipe can be cut in half for smaller groups or doubled if needed.
When taking this fruit to a cookout or picnic, I always bring two bowls.
Serve one and keep the other on ice in cooler for later.
Always a favorite at family gatherings.

title: pasta with grilled chicken, goat cheese, spinach and sun-dried
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together 2 tablespoons olive oil with lemon juice, basil and oregano.
Add chicken breasts.
Turn to coat evenly and marinate about 30 minutes.
Preheat the grill or broiler.
Cook pasta until al dente.

title: creamy beef and macaroni whip-up
directions: Brown ground beef in a big pan.
Boil noodles in a pot.
Mix noodles, spaghetti sauce and mayonnaise in with ground beef. Stir.
Sprinkle on desired amount of cheese.
Serve.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: This can be kept for months in tightly covered jar.

title: southwest salad
directions: Toss together first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Whisk together oil, lemon juice and salt; pour over black bean mixture, stirring gently to coat. Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: mo dip
directions: Brown meat; add taco seasoning. Cook 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Cook till cheese melts. Can be used as a soup or a dip.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and hot water and salt until stiff with an electric beater.
Beat egg white pouring water so they won't cook. Add sugar slowly and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon lemon extract.
Add flour slowly.
Continue beating; add baking powder last.
Bake as an angel food.
Slow for 1 hour.
Don't make the pan over half full or it will run over.

title: chicken delight
directions: Simmer chicken until done.
Remove meat from bone.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers and butter and place in buttered flat baking dish.
Brown crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham and cheese buns
directions: Trim fat and skin from ham.
Place ham on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Beat the egg until thick (about 5 minutes).
Fold in the mustard; brush over the ham.
Sprinkle with some pepper and 1/4 to 1/3 cup bread crumbs to coat.
Bake in 325° oven 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 hours (meat thermometer should read 140°).
Prepare Mustard Whip.
Serve with sliced ham.
Makes 16 to 24 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix together Cheddar cheese and flour.
Then add the half and half, eggs, crab meat, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Mix well.
Beat eggs; add milk and oil.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients.
Mix until dry ingredients are moist.
Don't overmix. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes in greased pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow all three cheeses to soften and add the chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce and garlic clove.
Mix to consistency of spread.
Form into a ball and refrigerate until semi-firm.
Roll in chopped parsley, chopped nuts or sprinkle with paprika.
Chill well and set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt until smooth.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Fold in cranberry sauce and Cool Whip.
Freeze in muffin tins lined with cupcake papers.
Makes about 18.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving on lettuce.

title: peanutty hot fudge cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add warm water, lemonade, nectar and pineapple juice. Stir well. Add cold water. Freeze in four equal size containers.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving to allow punch to thaw to a slushy consistency. Add ginger ale before serving. Yield: Approximately 40 servings.

title: pat's excellent soup
directions: Use enough mixed dry beans to make a 1/2-inch layer in a 3-quart saucepan.
Soak the beans overnight in the water or stock and with the spices stirred in.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bring it all to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer it, covered, for about 2 hours or until the vegetables are of desired consistency.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 crusts after it has been blended in a blender.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops with mushrooms
directions: In a paper bag, combine Parmesan, cornmeal, bread crumbs, garlic salt and oregano.
Melt butter in a skillet; dip each chop into butter.
Drain briefly, then shake each chop in the bag. Shake off excess coating and arrange chops on rack of a broiler pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven about 40 to 50 minutes. Meanwhile, heat the butter remaining in skillet over medium heat; add mushrooms and garlic and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in rosemary and cream and cook over high heat until liquid is reduced to about 1/4 cup.
Stir in green onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a bowl and pass at the table with pork chops.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add 1 cup sifted flour. Beat well, then add 1 cup sifted flour and beat well.
Place butter and milk in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour immediately over batter.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour depending on pan used, 10-inch cake pan or tube pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat potatoes until warm.
Mix all the ingredients in the potatoes and place in a baking dish.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend sugar and flour; add to eggs with remaining ingredients.
Turn into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
This mixture forms its own crust; no pie crust is needed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook
chicken and take off of the bone.
Cut soft margarine into
flour
until
it feels like corn meal.
Mix boiling liquid into
flour mixture, as if it were biscuit dough.
Roll out on a floured board, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch square pieces. Sprinkle flour over pieces before cooking.

title: s-p-m yummies
directions: Spread peanut butter on saltine crackers.
Top each with marshmallow.
Toast until marshmallow begins to brown.
Be careful marshmallows burn easily.

title: potato supreme
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Melt margarine and saute onions together. Combine remaining ingredients and place in a greased (use Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oreo dirt pudding
directions: Crunch up 1 package Oreos.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or bowl (save a handful of cookies for the top of dessert).
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix well and set aside.
In large bowl, combine Cool Whip, pudding and milk.
Combine small and large bowl ingredients.
Pour over Oreo crumbs.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Chill.

title: congo cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar, then cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares and it's ready to eat.

title: english peas
directions: Cook onion in butter slowly for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: spritz
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cream shortening until soft.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolks.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Chill.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Place popped corn in a large paper grocery bag. Combine brown sugar, light corn syrup, butter or margarine and salt in a 4-cup glass measuring cup and bring to boil on Full power.
Boil for 2 minutes; stir, then add baking soda and stir until foamy.
Pour over the popcorn.
Close the bag and shake well.
Cook on Full power for 45 seconds.
Shake again and cook 45 seconds.
Shake again and cook for 45 seconds.
Shake bag and cook for 30 seconds; shake again.
Cook for 30 seconds.
Shake again.
Allow to cool, then break up and enjoy.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini, celery, onion, water, oleo, salt and pepper 5 minutes and drain.
Add eggs, cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls about the size of marbles.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Saute the onion with the ground chuck. Add the pizza sauce. Spread on buns. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Heat in microwave for 1 minute or until cheese is melted.

title: green pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Cook peas according to package directions until tender. Drain.
Combine soup and water.
Gently mix in peas, pimentos and cheese, reserving some cheese for the top.
Line bottom of a lightly greased 3-quart casserole dish with asparagus.
Pour soup mixture over asparagus and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except zucchini.
Cut zucchini in pieces.
Drop into batter.
Drop in 375° oil and fry until brown.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding with syrup.
Gradually add egg and milk, stirring to blend.
Pour in pie shell, then add nuts on top.
Bake at 375° until top is firm and just begins to crack, about 40 minutes.
Cool at least 3 hours.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Sift together.
Add just enough milk to form a soft dough. Drop by teaspoon into broth.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Do not peek or you will have soggy dumplings.
Boiled ham bone and broth is good.

title: gran's clamchowder
directions: Steam open clams, cool and chop.
Fry
bacon until well done. Fry onion and celery until brown.
Use water from steaming for broth.
Add some water (to taste) to cut down broth.
To broth add carrots, celery, onions, tomatoes, crushed bacon and fat, pepper, thyme.
Bring to boil, then simmer until carrots are soft.
Then add chopped clams, simmer for 15 minutes longer.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot & cook until the meat is tender - 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
* Add mushrooms 20 minutes before end of cooking time serve over egg noodles.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in large saucepan.
Heat on stove over low heat until jello dissolves, do not boil.
Cool. Mix in buttermilk, pecans and cool whip until blended.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix in order; beat well.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients; save 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Put 1 cup sauce in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Place 3 noodles, then a layer of sauce, a layer of cheese mixture and layer of noodles, until all ingredients are used.
Finish with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered with clear wrap (vent), in microwave for 15 minutes.
Let stand inside microwave for another 5 minutes.
Real good.

title: chili
directions: Mix together and simmer for 2 hours.
Good on hamburgers or hot dogs.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini into thin slices, but do not peel.
Boil about 10 minutes and drain.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Add to zucchini.
Add 1/2 of stuffing mix to zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Line casserole with 4 or 5 buttered slices of bread, crusts trimmed.
Mix in bowl the potatoes, coarsely grated.
Add eggs, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Wet 2 slices of bread with water.
Squeeze dry.
Put all in casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Place chips in microwavable bowl.
Heat on High until melted. Add cinnamon and sweetened condensed milk.
Heat 1 minute longer. Stir.
Slice apples and dip.
This can be kept in the refrigerator and can be reheated until all is gone.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken
to
minutes
(save 1 cup broth). Break into
bite size pieces and lay on bottom of baking dish. Mix soup,
milk
and butter until smooth.
Pour over chicken. Mix about
1 cup of broth with dressing and spread over top of all. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all and chill. You may want to substitute 1/2 cup mayonnaise or 1/4 cup sour cream for part of the whipped salad dressing (adjust to taste).

title: seafood shells
directions: Wrap tortilla shells in foil and heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Fit each tortilla into a greased 10 ounce custard cup. Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in the oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Transfer tortilla shells to 3 serving plates.

title: crab supper pie
directions: Sprinkle cheese evenly over bottom of pastry shell.
Top with crabmeat; sprinkle with green onions.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel, dry mustard and mace.
Pour over crabmeat.
Top with almonds.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for about 45 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Gradually add milk and mix well.
Continue cooking until candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball stage).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla until blended.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in microwave.
Drizzle over each cluster. Cool.

title: hello dollies
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Press in a 9 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oven fried catfish with crunchy cornmeal crust
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Using a nonstick baking pan, brush the oil over the surface and set aside.
Place flour on wax paper.
Beat the egg white in a shallow bowl.
Combine cornmeal, salt and red pepper on second sheet of wax paper.
Dip the fish in flour; shake off excess.
Dip fish in egg white; shake excess.
Roll fish in cornmeal to coat and place on the baking pan.
Repeat with other fish.
Bake until bottoms of fish are browned and you can hear the fish sizzling.
Turn fish over and bake about 5 minutes more.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 2.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix meal, bacon drippings, eggs, milk and corn. Brown beef with onion; drain. Layer 1/2 of the batter in an 8 x 12-inch baking pan (greased). Put beef on batter. Sprinkle peppers and 1 cup cheese on beef. Top with remaining batter and 1 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sue's bourbon slushies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; freeze overnight. Stir and add cherries and freeze.

title: broccoli-mushroom-bisquick bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Mix Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk; pour evenly over soup mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: super lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add marinara sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Boil noodles and have ready.
Mix the following together in small bowl cottage cheese, beaten eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Place 1/2 noodles in 9 x 13-inch baking pan; spread 1/2 cottage cheese mixture.
Layer with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, then 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Add a few slices Mozzarella to top.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 c. warm water. Mix, in a separate bowl, 1 c. water, salt, sugar, and shortening. Add egg and the yeast mixture and mix. Gradually add flour until a medium stiff dough is formed; knead well. Pinch off small amounts of dough and place in well greased pan; let rise until double in size, about 30 minutes. Bake in a hot oven until golden brown.

title: pineapple lettuce salad
directions: To serve on a big platter, use a thick layer of lettuce, shredded.
With spatula spread mayonnaise over all of lettuce, as much as you like, and same with the shredded Velveeta. Next, put drained chunk pineapple over all and to decorate place red cherries on top.

title: italian love cake
directions: Make cake as box directs.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Spoon over unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool.

title: tommy's taco soup
directions: Brown onions and meat.
Drain fat.
Add all other ingredients. Do not drain any of these.

title: bugle dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender or with a mixer.
Serve with Bugles.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Heat oven to 325. Grease 2 loaf pans. In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Stir in zucchini, sugar, oil and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients by hand. Bake at 325° for 50-60 minutes or until fork comes out clean.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the onions and cook for 20 to 30 minutes over a low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the sugar and flour.
Cook another minute or two.
Add the stock gradually, season to taste and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: In shallow 2-quart glass casserole, combine all the ingredients.
Place chicken in marinade; turn several times. Cover tightly and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours, turning occasionally.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add Jell-O. Let cool.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.

title: sugar plum pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour one oblong pan or 2 (8-inch) square pans.

title: francis' salad
directions: Mix
pudding
with
enough of the fruit juices to make a paste like.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Drain all the fruit.

title: beef garden casserole
directions: Cook onion in small amount of fat until tender.
Add meat and salt.
Brown lightly.
Drain off grease.
Stir in vegetables and soup, heat to boil.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: hot 'n' spicy chicken kabobs
directions: In small saucepan, blanch green pepper in boiling water for 1 minute; drain.
Cut each chicken breast half into 4 pieces. Alternately thread chicken, green pepper and pineapple onto skewers.
In small bowl, combine 57 sauce and honey.
Brush kabobs with butter, then 57 sauce mixture.
Grill or broil kabobs, about 6 inches from heat, 12 to 14 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink in center, turning and brushing with 57 sauce mixture once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick french onion soup
directions: In a medium pan, saute onions in butter until golden and tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in flour; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, at least 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
If desired, top with Melba toast rounds or a slice of French bread and grated Parmesan cheese or grated Mozzarella cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings .

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in small amount of oil.
Place in large casserole dish. Sprinkle half the salt and pepper, place potatoes and apples. Sprinkle remaining salt and pepper.
Place onions in pan that was used for browning chops.
Saute them.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mix with water and pour over chops, apples and potatoes.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or potato chips or over a baked potato.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or same size shallow dish.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake for 15 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In small bowl combine horseradish, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer-sized pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cottage beef bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and rinse.
Set aside.
Saute ground beef. Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cottage cheese, sour cream and onions to noodles. Use a 2-quart round casserole dish and spray with Pam.
Spoon 1/2 noodle mixture into bottom of casserole, then spoon in 1/2 meat mixture over the noodles.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Make 1 or 2 days early.
Keep refrigerated until ready to bake.
Freeze also.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: individual scout pack
directions: On a long piece of heavy aluminum foil, place one half of vegetables.
Season meat with salt, pepper and Worcestershire. Top with meat and add remaining vegetables.
Fold up sides and ends of aluminum foil.
Seal foil well to avoid steam escaping. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes turning once.
If placed on a grill, cook 17 minutes on each side.

title: crunch cake
directions: Melt sugar and
margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add eggs and stir in one at a time.
Add vanilla and flour and stir in. Add nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour batter in. Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: martha washington jets
directions: Combine all ingredients except paraffin and chocolate.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Make into small balls. Melt 1/2 bar of paraffin with bitter chocolate.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and paraffin; place on waxed paper to firm up.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Cook sugar, milk, syrup and salt to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered slab or cookie sheets to cool.
These will not be flat, sugary cakes like "New Orleans style pralines, but will be creamy.

title: cheese and sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Add vegetables.
Continue cooking 5 minutes. Drain. Set aside to cool 10 minutes. Stir together sausage mixture, Velveeta cheese spread and bread cubes. Place in greased 8-inch square baking dish. Beat milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage mixture. Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: coconut cream torte cake
directions: Step 1:
Take flour, butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and chopped walnuts, mix ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and beat.
Pour into large well-greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done or toothpick comes out clean.

title: crunchy rotel salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Combine all ingredients and toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas in small bowl with fork; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix all other ingredients with mixer, then add mashed bananas.
Mixture will be lumpy from bananas. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch oblong pan and bake for 1 hour. Cool and ice with vanilla icing.

title: peppermint cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with soup, broth, chicken and green chilies.

title: tahitian ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, pork, crackers, onion, milk, egg, parsley and pepper.
Shape into patties.
Line in rows alternating with pineapple slices.
Bake in a slow oven at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.
Prepare brown sugar, syrup, vinegar and mustard.
Pour over rows and continue to bake for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix
ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: smothered "steak and onions"
directions: In large bowl combine meat, black pepper and 1/4 cup beef broth and bread crumbs.
Mix well with hands.
Form 6 patties.
Place patties in large skillet; brown on both sides.
Layer onions evenly over patties.
In a covered jar, combine remaining ingredients. Shake well.
Pour over onions and meat.
Lower heat.
Cover. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, vanilla, spices and salt.
Mix at medium speed until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each.
Pour over crust.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool.
Remove rim of pan.
Chill several hours.

title: double beefburger(makes 4 servings)
directions: Shape ground beef lightly into a patty in a large frying pan. Brown 5 minutes on each side, then break up into chunks.
Stir in green onions, garlic and paprika.
Cook 2 minutes.
Blend in flour, then stir in beef broth.
Simmer, stirring often, 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir about 1/2 cup of the hot mixture into sour cream, then stir back into remaining mixture in pan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until hot.
Spoon on top of split hamburger buns to serve open-face style.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Melt candy bar, marshmallows and milk over a low heat, stirring until smooth. Cool, then fold in whipped cream; pour into crust. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: roast beef with yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place standing rib beef roast, fat side up, on rib bones; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Insert meat thermometer into center of meat, making sure the pointed end does not touch bone or fat. Roast until thermometer reaches 140° for rare, 160° for medium or 170° for well done. Place roast on cutting board or warm platter and let stand 15 minutes for easier carving.

title: country cheddar crackers
directions: Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix throughly, then add dry ingredients which have been mixed and sifted together.
Add extract.
Put through a cookie press and bake in hot oven (400°) 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In saucepan, combine milk and butter; cut into pieces.
Heat until just lukewarm.
In mixing bowl, combine 1 egg and egg white, salt, sugar and 1/2 cup flour. Add remaining flour.
Beat into a stiff batter for 2 minutes at high speed if using mixer.
Spread into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle topping over the dough; cover.
Let rise in a warm place until almost doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Cut into squares.

title: best peanut brittle
directions: Stir.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Let harden and break up.
It's better to overcook this a little than to undercook it.
With practice, you will learn to cook this peanut brittle to perfection.
Store in covered container.

title: raisin pudding pie
directions: Pour into a baked pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: corn salad
directions: Put into large kettle and stir often, as it will stick easily.
Cook for 30 minutes after it starts to boil.
Put into jars and seal.

title: paella
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender with 2 teaspoons salt, the pepper, onion, parsley and celery.
Remove from broth; take chicken off bones in large pieces.
Strain broth and save.
Cook rice and garlic in olive oil until straw-colored.
Add 1 1/2 cups broth, saffron, peas, shrimp and 2 1/2 teaspoons salt together.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish; add sausages.
Bake for 1 hour in moderate oven.
Add clams or mussels and bake until clams open.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Put 4 tablespoons of the mix into a cup of boiling water.
Add a dash of whipped topping or vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
While hot from the oven, punch holes in cake; slowly pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Then do the same with caramel topping.
Let cake cool at room temperature.
When cake is completely cool, top with Cool Whip. Keep in refrigerator.
The longer this cake sits, the better it gets.

title: lemon-lime pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Butter and flour a 9x5x3 inch loaf pan. In a large mixer bowl cream butter until smooth, about 1 minute. Gradually add 1 1/2 cups of the sugar and beat until light and fluffy, 4-5 minutes. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition; beat in the grated lemon and lime zest. Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder onto a sheet of wax paper. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the butter mixture in 4 to 5 additions, beating on low speed until just blended after each addition. Spoon into prepared pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until cake tester inserted into the center comes out clean and the edges of the cake begin to pull away from the sides of the pan. Leave in pan to cool on rack for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small non aluminum sauce pan, combine the remaining 1/2 cup of sugar, the lemon juice and lime juice. Cook over moderate heat stirring until sugar dissolves, 1 to 2 minutes. Do not boil. Remove glaze from heat. Remove cake from pan and place on a rack. Place rack on wax paper, and while cake is still warm brush all over with the hot citrus glaze. Let cool completely. Wrap in plastic and then over wrap with aluminum foil. Let cake stand in a cool place for at least a day before slicing. The cake will improve overnight and will keep for up to a week if kept tightly wrapped.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add frozen orange juice until dissolved.
Add pineapple and oranges; let congeal.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in 1/2 cup water until water is gone.
Mix flour and sugar and stir in raisin mixture.
Add egg yolk to sour cream. Add cinnamon and salt.
Cook together until thickened.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Turn into baked pie shell and top with beaten egg whites.
Brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add extracts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix alternately with mangoes.
(Add lemon juice to mangoes.)
Last of all, add chopped nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 375°.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Place butter in a small pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in sour cream mixture. Add eggs.
Combine flour and salt; gradually add to yeast mixture. Mix well.
Cover and let rise to double size, about 1 hour. Punch down; shape into rolls.
Let rise to double size again. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Break eggs in dish with melted butter and mix together.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and buttermilk to egg mix and mix together well.
Pour mix into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: beet pickle
directions: Cook and skin beets.
Add sugar and spices to vinegar and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beets.
Boil for 5 minutes. Pack beets into hot Ball jars.
Cover with boiling syrup.
If not enough syrup to cover, add more vinegar.
Process for 5 minutes in hot water bath.

title: fearless fried mozzarella cheese sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Coat a baking sheet with olive oil spray and set aside. Place egg whites and bread crumbs in separate shallow bowls. Add Mozzarella cheese to egg whites to coat, turn. Transfer to bread crumbs and turn to coat, gently pressing crumbs into cheese to coat completely. Arrange Mozzarella sticks on prepared baking sheet. Spray with olive oil. Bake 5 minutes until golden brown.

title: egg casserole(breakfast)
directions: Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Brown bacon and chop in blender.
Add croutons to margarine (cups according to dryness desired).
Pour egg mixture over croutons.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle on bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered tostada dip
directions: Combine beans and chili powder.
Mix well.
Combine avocados, miracle whip, bacon, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Layer bean mixture, avocado mixture, olives, tomato, chilies and cheese in shallow bowl.
Serve with Tortilla Chips.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; mix until well blended. Add dry ingredients; sift together into a large bowl.
Spoon into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave rocky road
directions: Place chocolate in 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle. Microwave at High 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir until evenly melted.
Fold in marshmallows and walnuts; coat evenly.

title: cheesy hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 300 degrees until bubbly.

title: banana blueberry pudding pie
directions: Line pie plate with vanilla wafers; top with bananas and blueberries in large mixer bowl.
Beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
On low speed, beat in water and pudding mix until smooth.
Chill 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pie plate. Chill.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Beat after each addition until well blended.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 2 1/4 hours.
(Start with a cold oven.) Freezes well.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Add crushed pretzels and pat into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese. Add whipped cream and spread over pretzel mixture.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and mix in sliced strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.

title: simmons baked catfish
directions: In a skillet, saute bell pepper in butter for 5 minutes. Lightly stir in bread crumbs, mayonnaise and mustard until blended. Arrange fillets in buttered 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon crumb mixture on top of fish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Do not overbake.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate all night in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, the next day at 375° for 1 hour.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Combine meats, oats, tomato sauce, egg, spices and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Pack mixture onto bottom and halfway up sides of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Drain off excess fat.
Top meat mixture with spinach.
Arrange tomato slices over spinach.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer at 350° until cheese is golden brown and bubbly.
Serves 8.
This dish freezes well for advance preparation.

title: awesome coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. When cake is done, pierce all over with a skewer.
Heat cream of coconut to a boil; spoon about half over cake.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Combine crabmeat, parsley, pimiento and capers.
Blend dry mustard into mayonnaise; toss with crab mixture.
Fill each mushroom crown with about 2 teaspoonfuls or until full.
Bake at 375° until hot, about 10 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook until no longer pink.
Add Pasta Accents pasta and vegetables and water; stir to combine.
Cover; reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: If peaches are small, use 12 to 14.
The pie shell must be full.

title: buttermilk pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice to a boil in large saucepan. Remove from heat. Add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved. Cool and add pineapple and then buttermilk. Stir to combine. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a 13 x 9 dish and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil pineapple and Jell-O together for about 5 minutes. Chill.
Mix in other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer in glass 9 x 13-inch dish in order as listed.
Amount of ingredients to use varies to taste on items with asterisk (*).

title: no dough blueberry peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2 1/2-quart baking dish; set aside.
Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Spoon batter over butter in baking dish; do not stir. Combine peaches, blueberries and 1/2 cup sugar; spoon over batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: delicious quick bread
directions: Pour hot milk over cereal; let stand until cool.
Mix in egg and shortening.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add to cereal mixture.
Stir only to dampen flour.

title: peggy's lower fat biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix mayonnaise and margarine.
Cut in flour until crumbly.
Slowly add milk until right firmness.
Flour board and knead dough only slightly before rolling out and cutting biscuits.
(Use pastry brush to butter top.)
Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 8 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Pour part of chicken soup and enchilada sauce in casserole. Break up frozen tortillas.
Layer tortillas, onion, green chilies, chicken, tortillas and rest of soup and enchilada sauce.
Grate Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese; spread on top after casserole has cooked for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl stir together all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
