Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not overbake.
Remove cookies to a wire rack to cool. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: company breakfast
directions: Brown and crumble all sausage.
Put bread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Add grated cheese, then sausage, then soup.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: danish apple struedel
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt together.
Put yolk in cup and add milk to make 2/3 cup.
Roll out 1/2 of dough.
Use round, deep pizza pan.

title: lindaberg special
directions: Chop all vegetables; add salt and let stand for 2 hours.
Then add vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Do not heat. Put in jar; keep in refrigerator.
Take out to use as needed.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat all ingredients together, form like doughnuts and fry in deep fat.

title: rainbow nut bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and butterscotch chips together over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows, nuts and 1 cup of coconut.
Mix well.
Pat mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on remaining coconut.
Cool until firm in refrigerator.
Cut into small bars.
(Luscious.)

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine milk, egg, and margarine.
Add orange rind, juice, chopped apple and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Using a spoon, stir dry ingredients into the milk mixture until blended.
Drop by the spoonful into 1/2 in hot oil. Fry to a golden brown.
Drain.
Good with butter, apple butter or by themselves.

title: kathy's meat loaf
directions: Combine ground chuck, eggs, vegetable soup, tomato sauce, cracker crumbs and Worcestershire sauce in a large bowl; mix lightly until blended.
Shape into meat loaf.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until richly glazed.
For finished touch, mix small amount of brown sugar and honey for topping and heat meat loaf an additional fifteen minutes.

title: aunt mary deberry's kraut recipe
directions: Mix real good.	Pack
in
glass
or stone jug.	Be sure cabbage is under broth.
Let
stand for 4 or 5 days.
Check to see if sour enough.
If
it
is,
put
in clean jars and seal. Put in boiling water
bath
and
heat long enough to seal.
If cabbage is not sour
as
you
would like, let it stand another day.

title: mom's pineapple-coconut bars
directions: Layer as written.
Cook for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend sugar, oil and vanilla with eggs. Stir in zucchini. Sift together dry ingredients and combine with zucchini mixture. Fold in raisins and nuts. Pour into greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sybilla griffith's irish boil cake bread
directions: In a large saucepan, place shortening, 2 cups water, sugar, raisins, salt and spices.
Bring to a boil, boiling for 3 minutes. Let cool.
Add flour and baking powder alternately to raisin mixture.
Dissolve baking soda in 3 teaspoons water and add to mixture.
Mix in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Form all ingredients into 2 loaves or 4 small loaves.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and milk; mix.
Add margarine to the cooked potatoes; add with egg and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then set oven to 350° for another 30 to 40 minutes, or until firm.

title: triple bean salad piquant
directions: Drain all beans.
Toss vegetables in a large bowl.
Thoroughly mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and set in refrigerator for at least 8 hours, tossing several times. Serve chilled.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: First, dissolve jello in water.
Then fold in, all at once, the strawberries, pineapples, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into serving bowl.
Put in refrigerator and chill until firm. Remove from 'frige and spread top with sour cream.
Gently spoon remaining mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: In mixer, cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mash 3 bananas with potato masher to make approximately 1 cup.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas and mix.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Put into greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken neptune
directions: Pound chicken breast until thin on one half.
Put 1 ounce shrimp and 1 ounce crabmeat on pounded half of breast.
Fold over and pin together with toothpicks.
Dip in egg wash and then in breading mix.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve on bed of rice and top with Hollandaise sauce.
Serves 4.

title: brownies (mom's)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour and salt, sifted together.
Add egg and water that have been beaten together.
Put into wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° until edges brown.

title: cookie factory chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Then add the chips, grated candy bar and nuts.
Make golf ball-sized cookies 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with utility fork.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand 11 minutes and roll again in powdered sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove from the bone.
Place into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain vegetables and pour over chicken.
Pour in 2 cups chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.
Mix flour, margarine and milk together.
Pour over pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash.
Boil squash and onion just until onion becomes clear.
Drain well.
Place into baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over.
Mix soup with water as directed.
Put bread crumbs on top of squash mixture and pour soup over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Then add vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Stir in the chopped apples and oil. Heat oven to 350°.
Oil muffin tin and fill half full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add pineapple and eggs. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda, then add to other ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° until slightly brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook chicken broth, onions, celery and salt with half of the cooked potatoes.
Mash this mixture together.
Melt butter in saucepan; whisk flour in and gradually add milk.
Mix all together.
Add the other half of the potato chunks.

title: walnut chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (cornmeal, sugar, salt and flour). Beat 6 egg yolks, then stir in vanilla flavor, cream and margarine. Beat on 3 speed.
When finished mixing all ingredients together, then put in pie shell.
Cook pie shell for 9 minutes on 400°, then put in ingredients.
Put nuts on top of mixture, then cook on 425° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well.
Set overnight in the refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Heat carrots, potatoes and onion until boiling, about 5 minutes.
Add mixed vegetables.
Cook slowly until vegetables are tender.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Wrap
bacon
around
hot
dogs so ends overlap.
Lay in single layer with bacon ends down, in shallow dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown
sugar.
Cover dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: chocolate ribbon pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 Tbsp. milk in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping, spread over crust.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding.
Beat with wire whisk two minutes.
(Mix will be thick.)
Pour over cream cheese layer and refrigerate four hours.
Just before serving spread remaining whipped cream over pie.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix crushed chocolate wafers and margarine.
Press into a 10-inch pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Cool. Make custard of egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Melt chocolate.
Add 1 1/2 cups custard and 1 teaspoon vanilla; spread over chocolate crust.
Add gelatin, dissolved in cool water, to remaining warm custard.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cream of tartar.
Fold whites into custard.
Add the sherry.
Spread over black bottom.
Chill. Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate.

title: green chile stew
directions: Flour pork and brown in drippings.
Remove to pot; cook onions.
Add chile to meat and onions in pot.
Add remaining ingredients and stew until mixture is slightly thickened.
Freezes well.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: southwestern potato salad
directions: Microwave potatoes and water in covered micro-safe bowl on High for 14 to 16 minutes.
Stir after 8 minutes.
When done, drain potatoes and set aside.
Microwave cheeses and dressing in separate bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir into potatoes.
Add onions and bacon bits, mixing lightly.
Serve warm or refrigerated.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in boiling water.
When soft, put through strainer.
Scald milk; add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Add butter.
Cook 1 minute; sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: cheese ball
directions: All cheeses should be at room temperature.
Mix all except 1/2 pecans and parsley.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining pecans and parsley.
Let set in refrigerator over 6 hours.

title: fruit drink
directions: Mix ingredients in large punch bowl and serve with ice. Serves 12.

title: wiener-sauerkraut dish
directions: Put cut Linkettes on bottom of a buttered dish.
Put sauerkraut on top.
Place potatoes on top of sauerkraut.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and margarine and pour over the potatoes. Sprinkle paprika on top, if desired.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Blender may be used to chop and mix together.
Saves a lot of time.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers. Place in buttered casserole dish. Top with crackers. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground round.
Add onions and celery and cook 2 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and cook on low for 15 minutes, lid on. Serve on sandwich buns.
Enjoy.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Layer 1 package crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together soft cream cheese, egg and sugar; blend well.
Pour over crescent crust.
Carefully layer remaining rolls on top of filling.
Sprinkle small amount of cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cottage cheese and softened cream cheese together.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat eggs and add.
Add this combination and remainder of ingredients.
Mix well, put into a greased spring pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave in oven another 2 hours.

title: yummy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except apples and walnuts.
When all mixed add apples and walnuts.
Put in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan, (or loaf pan).
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
(Insert toothpick to see if done).

title: gwen's hot dog sauce(relish for hot dogs)
directions: Chop onions and brown onions, meat and butter.
Mix in all other ingredients and cover with 2 cups of water.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish with Pam or similar spray. Mix corn and beans together. Stir in other ingredients. Cover with crumbs and almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup cake mix for topping.
Add egg and margarine to remaining mix and blend well (pasty).
Spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In big mixing bowl, beat eggs; add bananas (mashed with fork). Mix good. Add sugar, salad oil and nuts; beat until well mixed. Add dry ingredients; mix until blended. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Beat up egg and add to meat.
Mix in onion and bread.
In separate bowl, mix together all dry ingredients.
Add this to meat mixture.
Add milk (first 1/4 cup); mixture should be wet.
If too dry, add more milk.
Roll into very small balls and brown in frying pan.
Add water to cover meatballs and simmer 30 minutes. When meatballs are done, thicken remaining water with cornstarch or flour for gravy.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in small saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add dry jello and vanilla.
Add strawberries and pour into a baked pie crust.

title: party mix
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Melt chocolate in double boiler on very low until very thin.
Pour in bowl and toss well until coated.
Then spread on wax paper until cool, then break up.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie plates lined with pie crust and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: priscilla's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, don't overboil.
Place on a cake rack to cool.

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush cookies in a ziploc bag.
Pour cold milk into large bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes after beating.
Stir in cool whip and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 Tbsp. of crushed cookies in each cup.
Fill the cup 3/4 full with pudding mixture and top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with gummy worms before serving.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all together, except 1 c. cheese.
Put in 9 x 13 pan. Put cup of cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: working mother cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto foil covered cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost when cool (optional).

title: tostitos dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Add chili, garlic salt, Tabasco sauce and oregano.
Stir in Velveeta cheese until melted.
Serve warm with Tostitos.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease and flour sheet.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes until done.
Turn out on dish towel, sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Cool 15 minutes.
Roll up with towel.
Unroll.
Spread filling in entire layer.
Roll back and chill.

title: chicken and bok choy soup
directions: Brown in oil the onion and mushrooms.
Add broth and simmer for 10 minutes. Add chicken and carrots and simmer another 15 minutes. Add bok choy and simmer about 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Let it stand overnight.
Some miniature marshmallows can be added, if desired.

title: holiday black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and halve them.
Save juice.
Dissolve jello in the hot water.
Add grape juice, Cola and 1/4 cup cherry juice. Cool.
When it begins to set, stir in pecans and cherries.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch dish or salad mold.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flours, soda and salt.
Use a very large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and milk.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
To bake, fill muffin tins that have been sprayed with Pam, 2/3 full.
Cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese pull-aparts
directions: Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch cake pan; mix in celery, dill, poppy or sesame seed and onion.
Cut biscuits into 1/4's, dip in butter and seed mixture.
Toss pieces with Parmesan cheese a few at a time.
Return to cake pan; bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: coconut crunch cake
directions: Pour into long greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done (30 minutes).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put 8 cups milk on stove; heat to boiling point.
Keep 1 cup of milk to mix in flour and pumpkin.
Separate egg whites; beat until stiff.
Add sugar and hot milk to flour, pumpkin, spices and egg yolk mixture.
Pour your hot mixture over egg whites; mix well.
Put into pie shells; bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Makes 8 (4) pies.

title: swedish walnut cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together thoroughly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes (test with toothpick for doneness).

title: sauce for mini-meatballs and wieners
directions: Blend ingredients.
Add meatballs or wieners and simmer until warm.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef,
chopped
onions
and bell pepper in skillet until done.
Drain and set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix all other ingredients, except mushrooms and cheese.
Pour meat mixture half and half into the pie shells.
Half mushrooms and cheese; put half and
half into pie shells.
Pour half of the milk mixture into each pie
shell.
Bake
at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, butter and sugar.
Alternate dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Do not overbeat.
Add blackberries.
Bake in floured and greased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all ingredients except pecans in blender container. Cover; blend 20 seconds or until fruits are finely chopped. Add pecans. Cover. Turn motor on and off several times to coarsely chop pecans. Chill.

title: stuffed peppers italiano
directions: Cut small opening around stem on top of peppers.
Rinse out seeds and place in pot.
Boil to soften slightly.
Meanwhile, mix chopped meat, boiled white rice, chopped onion, 1 1/2 cans Italian stewed tomatoes and seasoning.
Drain and place peppers in baking dish.
(Peppers can be stuffed, then cut 4 slits around each pepper.)
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, draining frequently.
Last 1/2 hour, pour remaining stewed tomatoes in dish covering peppers. Cook additional 10 to 15 minutes after spreading cheese on top so cheese can melt.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add grated lime rind and juice.
Beat egg yolks slightly; slowly add to jello.
Add milk, bitters (and sour cream, if you use only 1 egg yolk).
Stir until blended.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into jello mixture.
Add coloring and blend well.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Chill until firm. Garnish with twisted lime slices.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, cream of tartar and salt in an 8-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir well until foam disappears.
Pour over popped corn and nuts in a large roasting pan.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crumble the Oreo cookies, then mix the remaining ingredients together.
Pour the crumbled cookies on top.

title: tortilla chip casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl soup, chicken, chilies and milk.
Sprinkle half bag of chips in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half soup mix over chips; layer with cheese.
Then begin again with chips, soup and ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for half hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Cut off bread crusts.
Cut bread into squares of 4 or use round cookie cutter.
Mix curry and mayonnaise.
Toast rounds or squares on one side.
Butter other side.
Spread mayonnaise and curry on buttered side.
Top with a shrimp and a little of the mayonnaise-curry mix on the shrimp.
Top with shredded cheese. Run under broiler or in oven until bubbly.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Place cooked noodles in casserole dish.
Mix tuna, English peas and mushroom soup together and pour over noodles; bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt.
Brown chicken in hot oil, about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cook egg in butter in 10-inch frypan.
Push to one side and cook onion and mushrooms.
Add rice and soy sauce to taste.

title: methodist baked beans
directions: Chop and fry bacon.
Brown onions after chopping.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
May want to bake a little longer.
I mix brown sugar, vinegar, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce together to add to bean mixture.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given. Let set until ready to serve.
Then stir together good.
Enjoy.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In small bowl, beat together egg white and water.
Stir in pecans, stirring until all surfaces are moistened.
Mix together sugar, salt and spices; sprinkle over pecans, mixing well.

title: chicken-in-a-biscuit
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Add chicken, pimento, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Separate dinner roll dough into 2 rectangles, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Cut each rectangle into four 4 x 5-inch rectangles. Place heaping tablespoon chicken mixture on each.
Fold sides and ends of dough toward center; moisten edges with water and pinch to seal.
Shape into biscuits.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Put reserved stuffing on top of dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. You can sprinkle light cheese on top when done baking, before serving.

title: texas hash
directions: In large skillet, brown meat (do not drain).
Add peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: surprise pie
directions: Melt margarine and chips in a saucepan.
Sift together flour and sugar; add to margarine mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with plain crackers.

title: tomato-rice soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute onion and celery until very tender.
Mix tomatoes with chicken broth, onions, celery and butter in a blender jar; blend until smooth.
Pour into the saucepan and add the marjoram, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat.
Add rice and stir.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer about 15 or 20 minutes or until the rice is tender.
Serve with grated cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter.
Add green chiles, flour, half and half and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add uncooked, cleaned shrimp.
Simmer until shrimp begins to get done (don't cook too long because it will be baked again).
Cook fettucine al dente.
Put fettucine in a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and top with shrimp sauce and Parmesan cheese.

title: one pan potatoes and chicken
directions: While potatoes cook, in a large skillet toss and brown chicken in oil over high
heat 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Add salsa and corn; toss until heated through.
Time:
20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge(quick)
directions: Melt oleo over medium heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add powdered sugar, syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Note:
Can use crunchy peanut butter and omit walnuts.)
For easy pan removal, line pan with aluminum foil so it sticks up about 1 inch above the sides and grease.
When ready to cut into pieces, pull up on aluminum foil and remove from pan.
Pull aluminum foil away from candy and cut with sharp knife or pizza cutter.

title: sarah's country molasses cookies
directions: Beat together oil, molasses, sugar and egg.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Dip in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, Crisco and oleo until creamy. Separate eggs and add yolks, one at a time.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add coconut, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in roaster.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours. Do not stir.

title: haystacks
directions: Cook chili following directions on package mix.
Layer ingredients as follows: corn chips, hot chili, cheese, lettuce, onion, tomatoes, sour cream and olives.

title: festive broccoli
directions: Remove tough ends of lower stalks from broccoli; wash broccoli and separate into spears.
Arrange spears in a baking dish with stem ends toward outside of dish; add water.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine onions and butter in a microwave dish; cook, uncovered, at High for 2 minutes.
Stir in pimiento and remaining ingredients.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 1 minute.
Pour onion mixture over broccoli before serving.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in microwave 2 minutes; stir.
Heat another 1 to 2 minutes, until smooth.
Heat while cake in oven.

title: apple cake*
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except apples and nuts.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake 50 to 65 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and whipped topping together.
When the pretzel crust has cooled, place cream mixture on top of crust.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients and pour over first 5 ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: beef cheese log(especially for the holidays)
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon onto wax paper and shape into ball.
Wrap and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Grease 5 (No. 2) gold-lined cans and fill half full with mixture.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from cans and wrap in foil.
Keeps a long time; may be frozen, also.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; remove and drain.
In same pan, cook vegetables until tender.
Add sausage and cashews; cook 2 minutes, until warm.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at once and bake in layers for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press crumbs evenly onto bottom and about 3/4 inch up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, blending well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken breasts in enough water to cover.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups broth.
Remove bones and skin from chicken; cut into pieces.

title: festive roasted pepper dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended; refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers or chips.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk and juice until thickened.
Fold in Cool whip.
put in pie shell, cover and chill.
Spread Cool Whip on top when serving.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix broccoli, water, onion and butter in pan; bring to boil (hard).
In another pan, mix Cheez Whiz, soup and milk.
Bring to hard boil.
Mix together in one pan with rice; pour into casserole dish.
Cover with foil and lid.
Leave sitting on top of oven for 1 hour (not in oven).
Put oven at 250° or higher.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve over lettuce.

title: meg's cheesecake
directions: Combine and press into 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: old west dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: vegetables a la gartland
directions: Drain tomatoes overnight and towel dry.
Mix mayo, sour cream and curry well.
Stir mixture with tomatoes.
Top with fresh chives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 450° in muffin or cornstick pans.

title: hot spiced apple juice
directions: Mix all together in a large pot on stove.
Heat on low heat for 5 hours.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: cranberry nut bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Prepare cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Mix together.
In another bowl mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in orange juice and egg to moisten. Fold in the cranberry mixture.
Spoon into greased and floured pan. Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
With hand, roll in ball and put in center of 9-inch pie plate. Mash and spread dough to sides and in bottom. Flute edges. Bake in 325° oven until brown.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl; pour into buttered (or Pam) dish. Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
This is great for leftovers!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla together; pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Mix all together and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add about 1 tablespoon butter and teaspoon vanilla.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine and toss with crushed cracker crumbs.
Spread on top of casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk; squeeze out. Mix beef, bread, egg, garlic, cheese, salt and pepper. Mix with hands very thoroughly. Form into size meatballs desired. Place on baking sheet. Place in 375° oven until browned. Cook meatballs in your favorite spaghetti sauce slowly for 2 hours.

title: grandma b's soft gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and sorghum; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add flour, salt and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Whip egg whites until foamy; fold in cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Fry hamburger; heat pork and beans.
Take a large baking dish and put 1 layer of hamburger, 1 layer of beans and 1 layer of cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Place biscuits on top.
Put in oven on temperature that biscuits can calls for. Bake until brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and marshmallows in large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Melt and bring to a boil the margarine, shortening, cocoa and cola.
When mixture boils, pour over flour mixture.
Beat eggs, buttermilk (I put about a tablespoon of table vinegar in regular milk to make my buttermilk) and soda.
Add to mixture. Batter will be thin.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test center for doneness.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix everything together except sour cream and pour half the mixture into a dish. Refrigerate. When set, spread sour cream evenly over it and put rest of mixture on top.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Stir in 1 cup Rice Krispies.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Press with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: beef and vegetables with chinese noodles
directions: In large skillet heat corn oil; add beef and saute until almost brown, then add garlic and cook until soft.
Stir in frozen vegetables, soy sauce, ginger, contents of one flavor packet from soup and 2 cups of water.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix together 2 tablespoons of cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir into vegetable/beef mixture until mixture thickens.
Cook noodles per package directions. Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's good hot rolls
directions: Soak 2 pkgs yeast in 1/2 c warm water.
Melt 1/2 c margarine in 1 c hot water.
Add 1 c cold water, salt and sugar.
When lukewarm add yeast and well beaten eggs.
Add 7 1/2 c flour to mixture, 2 c at a time and vigorously after each addition.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Roll out and cut into rolls, placing in greased pan and let rise 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400 for 10 - 15 minutes or until dough is light brown.
Dough will keep several days in refrigerator, but should be worked down each day until used.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: real chinese wings
directions: Place all ingredients in a bottle and shake well.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Place in a pan and cook 1 hour at 350°.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Turn chicken after 1/2 hour. Enjoy!

title: apple crisp
directions: Place the apples in a buttered 10 x 6 x2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Mix together the flour, sugar and butter and drop mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: skor cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, but add the Skor bits.
Bake cake. When cake is done, poke holes in hot cake.
Pour half jar of caramel topping and can of milk over top.
Refrigerate until completely cool.
Top with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed Skor bar on top.
(Can use Heath bar or Heath bits.)

title: coastal chili
directions: In a 3-quart microwaveproof casserole, combine oil, garlic, onion, chili, cumin, oregano, cinnamon, salt, cayenne and black pepper. Cover with wax paper; cook on High for 3 minutes or until onion is tender. Add remaining ingredients, except scallops. Cover; cook on High 8 to 10 minutes until mixture is boiling. Stir well. Place scallops around outer rim of dish. Cover with wax paper. Cook for 15 minutes. Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with rice and a dollop of sour cream.

title: belgian pancakes
directions: Mix well buttermilk, eggs and cooking oil and add self-rising flour, sugar and baking soda.
Mix all together until well moistened.
Need not beat out all lumps.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in salt, mustard, flour and pepper until smooth.
Add milk; stir in cheese until melted.
Pour over macaroni and mix well.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: tuna dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Chill if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with oatmeal.
Roll in balls. Grease pan first time.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: half hour pudding
directions: Mix 1 cup brown sugar, flour, milk, baking powder, salt and raisins together.
Put into a deep dish.
Combine boiling water, butter, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and nutmeg.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
When put to bake, batter is on bottom and sauce on top.
When completed, these are reversed.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, beaten eggs and butter.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Pour into two 9-inch pie crusts.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot baked ham sandwiches
directions: Butter the bun on bottom half.
Sprinkle desired amount of brown sugar over the buttered bun, then top with a slice of ham and Swiss cheese.
Spread mustard on top half of bun.
Sprinkle poppy seeds on the mustard and onions.
Close sandwich and wrap in tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for around 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Combine broccoli and water and boil to crisp-tender.
Drain. Arrange broccoli in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Pour half of the mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over soup layer.
Top with remaining soup.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Scatter over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, cook beef until brown; drain well.
Add taco seasoning, garlic, cayenne and water. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes; set aside.
Sprinkle cornmeal in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole (preferably a baking stone). Place 6 tortillas in bottom of dish, overlapping and extending edges up slightly.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in pan.
Let boil for 9 minutes at mid-heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream. Add pecans.
Pour fudge into buttered pan. Cool before cutting.

title: bacon wrapped scallops
directions: Wrap each scallop with a piece of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Sprinkle with seasonings and lemon juice.
Place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 8 minutes or until bacon is crisp, turning once.
Serve immediately. Yields 4 servings. Prep time:
8 minutes.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake with raspberry topping
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Spray spring-form pan, 9 x 3-inch, with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs on bottom of pan.
Beat yogurt and cream cheese in medium bowl on medium speed until smooth.
Add sugar, milk, flour, vanilla and egg whites.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Place 1 cup of batter in bowl.
Beat in cocoa and extract until blended.
Spread batter over crumbs in pan. Drop chocolate batter by spoonfuls onto vanilla batter.
Swirl through batter with metal spatula for marbled effect.
Don't touch bottom!
Bake 1 hour.
Turn oven off.
Leave cake in oven 30 minutes, then remove it.
Cool 15 to 18 minutes.
Prepare Raspberry Topping.
Spread over cheesecake carefully.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: stuffed peppers supreme(green)
directions: Cut washed peppers in half and remove seeds and membrane. Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Place in buttered casserole. Brown beef and onion in oil and drain off fat.
Add 1 cup of the tomato sauce and seasonings and cooked rice.
Spoon mixture into green peppers, heaping full, then pour the rest of tomato sauce over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover. Sprinkle with grated cheese and buttered crumbs and bake 10 minutes more.

title: milk chocolate frosting
directions: Place chocolate in a microwave-safe container.
Microwave at 100% for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring halfway through cooking.
Stir in butter until smooth.
Spread over cookies or cookie bars.

title: yvetta's fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2 qt. saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling for five minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough for 1 hour before using.
Line pizza pan with foil.
Spread cookie dough onto pizza pan.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown at 375°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Allow cookie dough to cool, then turn over onto a plate.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto cookie crust.
Top with favorite fruit and enjoy.

title: reuben balls
directions: Mix corned beef, sauerkraut and cream cheese.
Form into little balls (50 to 60).
Dip into beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: baked chicken and pasta
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a shallow baking dish.
Cut bacon in 2-inch strips.
Layer over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour off some of drippings, if desired. Blend soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and continue baking another 30 minutes.

title: baked beans(serves 15)
directions: Cut bacon while partially frozen into strips; saute peppers, onions and bacon until done.
Add to beans and brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered.
Bake longer if needed.

title: banana pudding
directions: Reserve one cup of Cool Whip.
Mix pudding mix, milk, condensed milk and remaining Cool Whip.
Put alternating layers of cookies, banana slices and pudding mixture in bowl.
Spread the reserved Cool Whip on top.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve the 3 packages of jello in boiling water.
Let cool until slightly thickened, then add beets, pineapple and nuts.
